title: mushroom business
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion, celery, green pepper and season with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
When sauteed lightly, add the mayonnaise.
Butter six slices of bread on both sides and cut in 1-inch squares.
Put half of bread in casserole; add sauteed vegetables.
Add rest of buttered bread.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over all and refrigerate a few hours or overnight.

title: winter strawberries
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet. Add eggs, coconut, salt and dates. Cook and stir over medium low heat until mixture is thick and bubbles, 5 to 10 minutes. Remove from heat, stir in cereal, nuts and vanilla. Shape into Strawberry shapes. Roll in red sugar. Mix up a little butter icing tinted green to make a little leaf and stem. Very pretty and tasty. Well worth the effort.

title: 6-layer mexican dip
directions: *Or available already shredded is cheese just called "Mexican Cheese" or something like that which is a seasoned mixture of cheeses - that's what I use.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender or quart jar.
Blend or shake until frothy.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen beans in salted water; drain.
Combine milk, soup and pepper; pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can onions into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with 1/2 can onions and pimiento.
Bake 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate butterscotch bars
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix flour and soda; set aside.
In large bowl, mix sugar and butter with mixer. Add egg and vanilla; beat until light.
Add flour mixture, pecans and chocolate chips.
Blend on low until combined.
Put in pan and bake for 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cook, cut and serve.

title: glazed turkey kabob
directions: Preheat broiler.
Add water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup. Combine juice, brown sugar and soy sauce in small saucepan.
Bring to boil over heat.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 2 to 3 minutes. Set glaze aside.

title: fruited pork kebabs
directions: Note:
You will need 8 wooden skewers.

title: ham and pork loaf with peach mustard glaze
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Lightly grease loaf pan and set aside.

title: special holiday jello
directions: Rinse strawberries; pat dry.
Leave caps and stems (if present) intact.
With a sharp knife, make 4 or 5 slices in each berry from tip end almost to, but not through, cap.
Gently fan out berry as far as possible.
(Stem end of berry should remain intact.)

title: deb's dip
directions: Mix together and serve with tortilla chips.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Layer the ingredients in the order given in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon dressing for fruit salad
directions: Cook all ingredients over medium heat until transparent. Cool.
When ready to use, thin with favorite juice.

title: ann's pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease off.
Put in a baking dish. Top with sauce and cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla, beating to blend.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to first mixture and add squash.
Add nuts and raisins; spoon into slightly greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie(low-fat)
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, nuts, vanilla, salt and Egg Beaters.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake on middle shelf at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: dani's no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and salt to boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, let cool for 1 minute.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until peanut butter dissolves.
Add oats and stir well.
Spoon out on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: coconut-cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and cream cheese; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix Fruit Fresh in water according to package.
Soak apples for 10 to 15 minutes.
Dry with paper towels (they will stay for hours).
Grapes, pineapple or bananas can be used.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cook bacon, save grease; crumble.
Shred the cabbage. Cook cabbage in bacon grease until it is limp.
Add crumbled bacon. Serve hot.

title: potato casserole
directions: Add cheese and margarine to grated potatoes.
Toss.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: peach pudding(serves 6)
directions: Spread fruit over batter.
Over this, pour mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 cup boiling water.
Bake for 1/2 hour in moderate oven.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening, gradually adding sugar until light and fluffy and sugar is dissolved.
Add egg yolks, beating well.

Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add flour to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour. Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts, reserving 2 tablespoons of nuts for the top of cake.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fish-vegetable chowder
directions: Cube, cook and drain carrots, potatoes, onion and celery. Blend together the butter and flour.
Make a thin sauce by adding butter mixture to milk and bringing to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in cheese and add marjoram.
Add vegetables and fish.
Season to taste.
Reheat.
Makes 1 gallon of soup.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: In large casserole, place lettuce.
Layer the onion, celery, water chestnuts and peas.
Spread mayonnaise and sugar mixture over top like frosting.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with bacon bits before serving.

title: mandarin orange pie #2
directions: Mix milk, lemon
juice and Cool Whip.
Drain and cut up oranges.
Add oranges and nuts to milk mixture.
Pour into pie shells and refrigerate.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to the box directions.
Meanwhile mix the first six ingredients together in a bowl.
Stuff shells with mixture.
Put into large lasagna pan.
Pour chicken soup mix on top.
Bake at 350 for 30-45 minutes.

title: my mother's broccoli & cheese cornbread
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Leave small amount in pan and pour the rest into cornbread mix, cheese, onion, broccoli and eggs mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: betty's butterscotch "gogo fudge"(for kids to make)
directions: Combine butterscotch morsels, peanut butter on top of double boiler (make sure water on bottom of double boiler is hot, but no boiling).
Stir mixture until it melts and is smooth.
Now add sweetened condensed milk; blend together.
Put into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill.
Makes 64 (1-inch) pieces.
Store in covered container.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream Crisco, peanut butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into balls.
Roll balls in sugar and place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove and top with a Hershey's Kiss (pressed down firmly so cookie cracks edge).
Bake 2 to 5 minutes until brown.

title: w. w. pina colada pie
directions: Mix pineapple,
pudding mix and coconut flavoring.
Stir. Add yogurt and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add to crust.
Let stand in refrigerator until set.
Very good.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo.
Pour melted mixture over cereal in a bowl.
Shake powdered sugar on the coated cereal.
It works well to shake this in a paper sack.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix thoroughly and add enough flour to hold together.
Drop from spoon in hot lard on griddle.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In a small skillet, melt 1/4 cup butter and saute onion until soft but not brown.
In a saucepan bring chicken broth to a boil; add sauteed onion, rice, salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole; cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
In a small saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter and saute almonds 2 to 3 minutes.
Just before serving, toss rice and sprinkle nuts over top.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric blender on slow speed, then mix on high speed until you have a smooth texture.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in 4 pieces. Dip in mixture of sugar and cinnamon and spread evenly in Bundt pan.
Melt butter, brown sugar and remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Heat over burner until smooth. Spread over biscuits and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hop, skip and go naked
directions: Mix well.
Really tastes good!
Serves 30 people for 1 hour.

title: stir-fry pizza
directions: Coarsely chop pepper, onion and tomato.
Prepare cheese pizza according to package directions. Do not bake. Spray a medium size skillet with Pam; heat. Over medium heat, stir-fry mushrooms, pepper and onion for 1 minute.
Stir in tomato.
Place vegetable mixture over grated cheese on unbaked pizza crust. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 18 to 22 minutes or until crust is desired brownness.

title: hot tuna and egg buns
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine tuna, olives, cheese, eggs, mayonnaise, pickle relish, onion and salt; mix well. Spoon into buns. Wrap each in foil.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: cran-apple mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin with water.
Stir in cranberry sauce until melted.
Mix in applesauce.
Pour into 5 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 10 servings.

title: fried spaghetti
directions: In a skillet melt margarine.
Break pasta into thirds and add to skillet.
Brown the noodles (as close to burnt as possible). Add 2 cups chicken broth and enjoy the sizzle!
Season to taste. Boil until noodles are slightly underdone, adding any remaining broth as necessary.

title: beef wellington
directions: Place on shallow roasting pan. Place in oven at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: miniature date puffs
directions: Stuff dates with nuts.
Make pastry with other ingredients. Roll pastry thin and cut with small biscuit cutter.
Wrap pastry around dates.
Press edges together.
Bake in 375° oven 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Combine with orange juice.
Add sugar, butter and nuts.
Mix well and shape into small balls; roll in coconut and refrigerate.

title: neapolitan cake
directions: Split cake horizontally into 4 equal layers and place bottom cake layer on a serving plate; set aside.
Slice ice cream into thirds according to flavors.

title: deviled green beans
directions: Cook beans until tender; drain.
Melt butter and cook onions until glossy.
Add sugar, prepared mustard, salt, pepper and instant bouillon which has been dissolved in 2 tablespoons water. Blend well and let simmer just until mixed.
Add to the cooked beans and simmer 10 minutes longer or until flavor is absorbed in the beans.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch spring pan; dust with graham cracker crumbs. Sieve cottage cheese into a large mixing bowl (I use a blender). Add cream cheese.
Beat on high speed until well blended and creamy.
Blend in sugar, then eggs.
Reduce speed to low.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugah, buttah, milk and cocoa 'n boil fur 1 1/2 minutes...remove 'n add oatmeal, peanut buttah and vanillah. Blend, beat 'n drap by the spoonful on wax papur...no need to bake cauz they'll harden by themselves!

title: chicken and spinach lasagna
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in 1 tablespoon butter and set aside.
In small bowl, mix together Ricotta and cottage cheeses and set aside.
Melt butter in large saucepan and add garlic. Saute 1 minute.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cook until bubbly.
Add milk and chicken broth.
Cook until thickened, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add Mozzarella, Parmesan, basil and oregano.
Stir until cheese is melted. Add onion and mushroom mixture.
Spoon a small amount of sauce into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with a layer of noodles, then a layer of cheese mixture followed by a layer of spinach, then a layer of chicken.
Repeat layers, ending with a sauce layer.
Top with remaining Parmesan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: pat's chicken pot pie
directions: Mix broth, soup, vegetables, chicken, salt and pepper.
Pour into long pan.

title: lime-strawberry surprise
directions: Prepare lime jello as directed on package.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in drained crushed pineapple.
Pour in 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: thousand island salad dressing
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Serve over salad greens.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: gold burgers(meatballs)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Put in sauce and simmer at 350° for 2 hours.

title: sweet snack mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine popcorn, cereal and peanuts.
Melt coating in microwave according to package directions.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over popcorn mixture and stir to coat. Spread evenly on waxed paper.
Allow to set for at least 2 hours. Store in airtight container.
Yields 5 to 6 quarts.

title: $10.00 pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 370°.
Place butter in casserole dish and melt.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted butter and then fruit over batter.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough into 11 x 15-inch pan and bake 10 minutes; cool.
Combine sugar and cream cheese and spread on cookie.
Top with your favorite fruits in an attractive fashion.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook over low heat in a large saucepan for about 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except for spaghetti.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
If sauce appears too thick, add water.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone it and place chicken in bottom of casserole dish (sprayed with Pam).
Mix cream of chicken and cream of mushroom together.
Spread over the chicken.
Add the cheese over the top of soup.
Use 1 cup of broth before stuffing mix.
Add stuffing mix on top and melt the butter and pour on top.
Bake in oven or until brown.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain. Place broccoli and drained water chestnuts in alternate layers in a casserole.
Top with undiluted soup.
Bake in a slow oven at 300°
for 30 minutes.
A few minutes before dish is done, sprinkle crushed onion rings over top and bake a few more minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: Bring water to boil; stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until all water is absorbed.

title: dad's special
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and seasonings.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, lay half of noodles, meat mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers of noodles and meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese; continue baking until melted.

title: honey chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put wings on large baking dish.
Season with fresh ground pepper.
Mix ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake 45 minutes.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Blend lemonade into Eagle Brand milk, then blend in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies or 1 large oblong Pyrex dish.
Keep chilled.

title: layered salad
directions: In a long dish, place shredded lettuce, bell pepper (sliced or chopped) and onion (sliced or chopped).
Add boiled eggs (sliced) on top of this.
Add the English peas last.
Spread over all of this the mayonnaise.
Better if refrigerated overnight.
Before serving, add the bacon bits on top.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine dry ingredients, then combine all other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet to make about 32 to 34 cookies.
Bake about 15 to 20 minutes, watching carefully to avoid overbrowning.
Remove from pan when done.

title: gold punch(yields 50 cups)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: broccoli ramen salad
directions: Mix together
the oil, vinegar, sugar and pkg. of seasonings and pour over dry ingredients.
Toss.
Let stand for 2-3 hours.

title: tex mex corn chowder
directions: Brown the onions, hash browns and garlic in oil for three minutes.
Mix everything together in pot and cook.Top with crumbled bacon, shredded cheese (jack/cheddar is good), dollop of sour cream, crushed cool ranch doritos.

title: cheese balls or west coast cheeseburgers
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Divide into 10 portions and pat meat around a block of cheese.
Place into a greased pan.
Add brown sugar to 1 cup tomato juice and pour over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: thai sweet and sour sauce
directions: Put the water, sugar, salt and vinegar in a small pot.
Using low heat, bring slowly to a boil.
Add ketchup and stir.
Add cornstarch gradually, stirring until it thickens.
Remove from heat and cool.
Put in a jar and cover.
Use for sweet and sour sauce or as a sauce for fried won ton.

title: parmesan pillows
directions: Hard boil the desired number of eggs.
Shell eggs and cover in half pickle juice and half beet juice.
Place in refrigerator 3 to 4 days.
Drain and serve with garnish.

title: special brownies
directions: Combine cake mix, butter, evaporated milk and chopped nuts. Mix well.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press half the mixture into pan and bake 5 to 7 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels over low heat, stirring in 1/3 cup milk.
Pour melted caramels over partially baked layer.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of caramel layer.
Crumble remaining cake mixture over top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: the "best" barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Turn down and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours until thick and smells full bodied. You can put into crock and simmer 5 to 8 hours.
Strain if you wish and pour into pint jars and freeze.
It keeps in refrigerator 3 to 4 weeks.
This recipe may be doubled.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring sugars and syrup to a boil.
Add peanut butter and peanuts; stir until melted.
Add cereal mix to cover.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and spread over top of bars. Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.
Cut into squares.

title: company cake
directions: Cream together shortening and 1/2 cup sugar; add egg yolks. Sift flour, baking soda and salt together; add to creamed mixture with milk and vanilla.
Beat.
Spread into greased layer tins. Beat whites of eggs with pinch of salt until stiff.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, continually beating.
Spread meringue on top of each layer of batter.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake immediately at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal summer squash delight
directions: Mix all together and pour into sprayed casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with 3/4 cup cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese (grated) and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add chilies, corn, cheese, and bacon onion seasonings; blend well.
Sift together flour, corn meal and baking powder.
Add to corn mixture, blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; preheat oven to 350°.
Reduce oven to 300° when ready to cook corn bread.
Bake for 1 hour. Makes 12 squares (3 x 2 1/2-inch.

title: light banana bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, baking powder and nutmeg.
In a mixing bowl beat together egg whites, sugar and banana.
Add oil and mix well.
Stir flour mixture into banana mixture.
Spray an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with nonstick coating. Transfer batter to prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly on a wire rack.
Makes one loaf.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding slowly, beat until thick.
Fold in cool whip.
Grease a 13x9x2 inch dish.
Place layer of whole graham crackers on bottom of dish.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mix over graham crackers.
Place another layer of graham crackers on top of pudding.
Pour remaining 1/2 of pudding then cover with graham crackers.

title: crab imperial with cheese
directions: Make white sauce with first 4 ingredients.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Fold in crabmeat, gently.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice meatballs
directions: Combine rice with beef, egg, onion, salt, marjoram, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Mix lightly.
Shape into 18 balls and place in skillet.
Add sugar to rest of tomato juice.
Pour over meatballs.
Bring to boil.
Reduce and simmer 15 minutes.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in tube pan that has been rubbed with margarine and lightly floured.
Cool in pan on rack and remove to plate.

title: oven-fried potatoes(french fries)
directions: You will need Pam cooking spray and a 15 x 10 x 1-inch cookie sheet.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Mix cold water and cornstarch. Cook until thick and clear. Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Put sliced strawberries in pie crust. Sprinkle with Equal.
Pour jello over berries. Chill.

title: coconut candy
directions: Mix the powdered sugar and Eagle Brand milk well and add the coconut. Mix in another bowl the pecans and melted oleo. Add the two mixtures together. Put mixture in the refrigerator to chill. Roll out into small balls to dip.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Put chops in bottom of dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered, at 350°.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Marinate chicken for a few hours or overnight. Discard marinade. Grill or broil chicken until juices run clear.

title: gran's noodles
directions: Sift flour into bowl.
Add 3 egg yolks.
Start beating with a fork gently.
As you beat, flour will blend with the yolks. Continue beating until dough is very stiff.
Flour pastry board and start rolling out the dough.
Keep flour under the dough or else it will stick to the board.
Roll until noodles are very thin.
Dry for 2 or 3 hours or longer.
Cut into 2-inch wide strips or as you desire.
Use immediately or else store in the refrigerator.
Cook in chicken or beef broth until tender and done.
This makes a big batch of noodles.

title: strawberry candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Shape in bell shapes and roll in red candy sugar.
Use green pipe cleaners and leaf for decoration.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Add to first mixture.
Line pot with 1-inch of cookie crumbs, then 1-inch of filling, ending with cookie crumbs.
Gummy worms are inserted while layering with a couple peeping through the top layer.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix jello, pineapple and sugar.
Heat this until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat when mixture is dissolved.
Cool at room temperature (for about 1 hour).
Add cool whip and buttermilk. Mix well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients; add cream mixture alternately with buttermilk and jam.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° in tube pan.

title: pina colada cheesecake
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except coconut and pineapple.
Mix thoroughly with mixer.
Pour mixture in two to three portions into blender.
Add coconut and blend well. Blending should be done in several small portions.
Grease 9-inch spring-form pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Carefully place drained pineapple on top.
Place in roasting pan half filled with water. Bake for 1 hour at 450°.
Let set for 2 to 3 hours.
This cheesecake can be frozen for 2 to 3 months.
Enjoy!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy light.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly, but well.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and soda.
Mix until blended.
Add nuts.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Superb on fruits and vegetables.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Put corn syrup and peanut butter in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies and stir well. Press mixture in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Put down evenly. Melt together chocolate chips and butterscotch chips. Spread over Rice Krispies mixture.

title: teriyaki beef jerky
directions: Will need dehydrator and top and 5 dehydrator trays.

title: pinwheels
directions: Blend cream cheese, onion, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce until of spreading consistency.
Add parsley; mix well. Separate meat slices.
Lay out 5 slices, slightly overlapping on an 18-inch piece of foil.
Lay out 2 more rows to form a rectangle of meat.
Spread with cheese mixture.
Roll up as jelly roll, using foil to bring up meat at beginning of roll.
Use fingers to roll until complete.
Chill.
Just before serving, slice into 1-inch slices.

title: chicken soup
directions: In large pot, simmer chicken, celery, carrot, onion, bouillon, and pepper until chicken shreds easily (1-1 1/2 hours). Remove chicken, shred. Bring broth to boil. Cook noodles in broth about 6 minutes. Stir in undiluted soup. Stir gently to dissolve lumps. Add shredded chicken, red pepper flakes and fresh black pepper.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in hot oil, add garlic.
Cook until garlic is yellow.
Add soy sauce, salt and 1/2 cup water.
Cook 45 minutes. Add vegetables.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch blended in 2 cups water.
Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes.
Serve over hot fluffy rice or noodles.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: Spread the chicken breasts with a mixture of the mustard, oil, tarragon and garlic.
Roll the chicken breasts in the bread crumbs. Bake at 450° for 14 minutes.

title: tomato salsa
directions: Grind tomatoes, onion and pepper in food processor.
Add vinegar and salt.
Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: chocolate coconut balls
directions: Melt margarine slowly, add milk, coconut, and nuts.
Add sugar and salt; mix well.
Store in refrigerator until stiff, (should be overnight), make balls, after making balls, set back in refrigerator until very stiff, melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double broiler.
Dip candy in chocolate with a toothpick, then fill toothpick holes with a drop of chocolate.

title: dijon glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter in a medium saucepan. Add the next 5 ingredients and saute over medium heat until vegetables begin to brown, about 5 minutes.
Set aside.

title: sweet and sour potato salad(12 to 15 servings)
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover; cook 30 minutes. Drain; cool slightly.
Peel and quarter.
Cook bacon until crisp, drain and set aside.
Cook onions until soft and clear.
Combine eggs, vinegar and sugar in a small saucepan; cook over moderate heat.
Stir constantly until thickened (about 4 minutes) until temperature reaches 160°.
Combine potatoes, bacon and onion.
Pour vinegar mixture over potato mixture.
Toss gently.
Serve immediately.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O and boiling water well. Add the cranberry sauce, pineapple and pecans.
Let congeal in refrigerator and top with the following topping.

title: holiday ribbon ring
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour 1 1/2 cups into 6 cup round Tupperware ring mold.
Chill until set, but not firm, about 15 minutes.
Chill remaining gelatin in bowl.
Gradually blend in 1/3 cup of sour cream and spoon over gelatin in mold.
Chill until set, but not firm.
Repeat with lime gelatin, remaining 2 1/2 cups water and 1/3 cup sour cream, chilling dissolved gelatin before measuring and pouring into mold. Chill at least 2 hours.
Unmold.
Makes 12 servings.

title: lemon-lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Let cool, then add other ingredients.
Chill.

title: southwestern chicken or turkey
directions: Fry meat in oil on high heat for 3 minutes, or until brown. Stir in chili powder and cumin.
Remove chicken or turkey from skillet.
Add bell pepper and onion; stir-fry about 3 minutes. Return meat to skillet; stir in corn and salsa.
Stir-fry until thoroughly heated.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: "lightened" manicotti with cheese filling(makes 8 servings)
directions: Prepare manicotti according to package directions.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: easy chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix tomatoes, beans and chili powder.
Simmer.
No mistakes.

title: strawberry tiramisu torte
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla yogurt, powdered sugar and vanilla extract together.
Slice the angel food cake into 3 layers.
Sift the unsweetened cocoa onto a cake plate.
Place bottom layer of cake in plate.
Drizzle 1/3 Espresso over cake. Cover with layer of sliced strawberries and put half of the cream cheese mixture over strawberries.
Repeat with second layer of cake.
Add third layer and sprinkle top with cocoa and powdered sugar.
Cover and chill.

title: dreamsicle salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water. Let set until shaky.
Beat cream cheese and add Cool Whip.
Slowly pour in Jell-O and mix well.
Put in refrigerator until set. Serves 10 to 12.

title: nonfat dip
directions: Mix and let stand in refrigerator for at least 1 to 2 hours.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with pineapple, then Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: shipwreck
directions: Brown ground beef or ground turkey in pan and drain off excess grease and set beef aside.

Cook rice as directed on box, then in large skillet on top of stove put some ground beef on bottom of pan and a layer of rice, then a layer of potatoes and on top put some slices of onions and on top of this put some tomatoes and salt and pepper.
Now repeat all of this for your second layer and end up with tomatoes on top.
Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl pudding cake
directions: Pull apart cake into bite-size pieces.
Place in a large glass bowl.
Mix together yogurt, Cool Whip and box of pudding.
Pour this mixture over cake and toss until cake is covered good.
Mix the Jell-O with 2 cups of boiling water (not cold water).
Add strawberries while still frozen.
Stir until berries are thawed. Pour over pudding mixture.
Refrigerate overnight (or can be done early morning for evening meal).

title: el dorado eggs
directions: Use ovenproof skillet (approximately 2 to 3-quarts).
Combine taco seasoning mix, tomatoes, green peppers and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove rolls from package and separate into 4 rectangles.
Sprinkle each rectangle with 1/4 of the cheese.
Roll up tightly, jellyroll fashion, and slice each roll into 3 sections.
Combine eggs, sour cream, salt and pepper. Remove tomato mixture from heat.
Carefully spoon egg mixture over it while it is still hot.
Place biscuit spirals on egg mixture and sprinkle each with poppy seed.
Dot each biscuit spiral with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 60 minutes until biscuits are brown and egg mixture is firm.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put layer of lasagna noodles in bottom of pan.
Put browned hamburger and onions on noodles, some spaghetti sauce, then another layer of noodles, more hamburger and sauce.
Push all down into the liquid (hot water), cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Take foil off.
Add both the cheeses over top.
Bake for 15 minutes more, uncovered.
Take out.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: green bean salad
directions: In large bowl, mix together green beans, peas, celery, green pepper, pimentos and onions.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar, vinegar, oil and salt.
Pour over bean mixture and gently stir. Cover and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Pour liquid off 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken delight casserole
directions: Stir the ingredients.
Place in dish.
Sprinkle some stuffing mix on top (optional).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over melted margarine, pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips, then coconut and lastly nuts.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut in squares.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: "hot fudge sauce"
directions: In microwave, melt chips and margarine.
Add sugar.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes until thickens.
Add vanilla.
Wonderful over cake or ice cream.
Will keep in refrigerator for a month.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix and set aside for 15 minutes.
Make large marble sized balls.
Freeze before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Boil water.
Put noodles in pot.
Cook for 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Return noodles to pot.
Add the can of cheese to noodles; mix well.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine strawberries and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover and let stand in the refrigerator at least 1 hour.

title: shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter until light and fluffy. Blend in sugar and beat well.
Add cornstarch and blend.
Then add flour a little at a time until blended.
Pat dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prick well with a fork.
Can be sprinkled with colored sugar, if desired.
Bake for 1 hour or until set.
Turn off oven.
Cut into squares with sharp knife.
Return to oven for 15 minutes to dry edges.
Remove from pan when cool.
Dough may be rolled into 1-inch balls and flattened.
Bake until done.

title: diet workshop mayonnaise
directions: Blend at low speed 1 minute.

title: party popcorn cake
directions: In microwave oven melt together butter, oil, marshmallows and caramels.
Place popcorn and peanuts in large mixing bowl.
Add melted ingredients and stir together until popcorn and peanuts are evenly coated.
Add candies last.
Press firmly into oiled 12 cup Bundt pan.
Let cool.
Remove.
Let set overnight for easier slicing.

title: yam casserole
directions: Place yams in baking dish.
Mix salt, sugar, spices, butter and cream.
Pour over yams.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple butter pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, cornstarch, cinnamon, salt and apple butter; mix well.
Add milk gradually; blend.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Boil 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Spoon onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and green pepper; saute lightly.
Drain excess fat from pan.
Stir in soup, salt and thyme.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole.
Place potatoes in mounds around edge of casserole.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly and potatoes are lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cauliflower-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain cauliflower and broccoli.
Mix eggs, salad dressing, soup, stuffing mix and onion.
Melt margarine and pour in casserole.
Add broccoli and cauliflower.
Pour over other ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine potatoes, soup, onion, cheese, salt and sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Sprinkle corn flakes on top; drizzle melted margarine over them. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: *(Or can use 1 cup of mayo or 1 c. Miracle Whip.)

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on, then peel.
Grate or dice finely. Combine all ingredients and place in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. This may be prepared in advance.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Place ingredients in buttered casserole dish.

title: irma's brunswick stew
directions: Put chicken and pork in a large pot with 3 cups of water. Steam until tender and well done.
Shred pork and chicken.
Cook onions, tomatoes, catsup, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and salt in 2 cups broth from the chicken and pork.
Cook 2 hours with the top on.
Add creamed corn and shredded meat.
Cook until the right thickness with top on for about 2 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion; drain grease.
Drain green beans and mix with meat and onion and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Top with creamed potatoes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water (110°).
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour; beat well.
Beat in yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough, beating well.
Place in greased bowl, turning over to greased surface.
Cover.
Chill at least 2 hours or up to 4 to 5 days.
About 2 hours before serving, shape the dough as desired on floured surface.
Put in greased pan.
Cover; let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine ground zucchini and ground onions; add ground bell peppers.
Sprinkle with pickle salt.
Cover mixture and let set overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Squeeze as dry as possible.
In a large pot, add to ground mixture the vinegar, white sugar, dry mustard, nutmeg, turmeric, cornstarch and pepper.
Cook for 30 minutes; stir occasionally.
Be careful not to scorch.
Seal in hot jars.
Makes 7 pints.

title: gingerbread
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar, molasses, 2 beaten eggs and flour.
Combine.
Then add remainder of ingredients. Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: mr. tim's corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour into greased baking pan. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: frosty pumpkin sandwich cookies
directions: Mix pumpkin and Marshmallow Creme, then add the ice cream. Pour into a baking pan.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours.
Cut into squares. Place ice cream mixture between 2 cookies.
Makes 15 sandwich cookies.

title: shrimp buns
directions: Split 4 or 5 hamburger buns and butter them.
Pile each half with the mixture.
Place open-face on a pan and broil 5 or 10 minutes, until cheese bubbles.
Serve immediately.

title: date bread
directions: Sprinkle soda over dates.
Pour boiling water over both. Combine sugar, salt, fat and egg.
Add nuts and date mixture and the sifted flour.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water. Cook until forms a good soft ball. Pour 1/3 of this into stiffly beaten egg whites. Put remaining syrup back on stove and cook until it forms a very firm ball. Pour 1/3 of this over egg whites; beat again for about 5 minutes with electric mixer. Cook remaining syrup until it spins a thread and looks stringy when dropped in water. Pour this over egg whites and beat a few more minutes with electric mixer. Add vanilla, salt and pecans if desired. Then beat by hand slowly until it loses the shine or until ready to drop from spoon. Spoon onto wax paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute first 3 items then add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz. Stir until smooth, then add Minute rice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Fold in vanilla, lemon extract and milk.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan and place in a cold oven.
Turn oven onto 325° and bake for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: linda's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour and cream alternately. Add flavoring.
Place in cold oven and bake in greased and paper lined 9-inch tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Let cool on rack a few minutes. Turn out to finish cooling. Serves 24.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Measure 1 1/2 cups of the sifted flour into a large bowl and add yeast.
Blend at number 3 speed for 1/2 minute with mixer. Combine milk, 1/2 cup water, oil, sugar and salt in small saucepan. Heat on low heat until mixture is just warm.

title: mamaw's chocolate gravy
directions: Put in iron skillet and mix in 2 cups milk, half stick butter and let ingredients get thick.
Add dash of salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: zucchini creole
directions: Dice or slice zucchini squash.	Cook in boiling, salted water until tender.
Do not
peel.
Drain and place in greased casserole in alternate layers with sliced tomatoes and chopped or sliced onions.
Dot
each	layer
with butter or margarine, salt and brown sugar.
Top with buttered bread crumbs, crushed cornflakes or crushed crackers
and
grated cheese.
Bake in a moderately hot oven (400°) about 20 minutes.

title: lorcan's lamb stew
directions: Marinate lamb with Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and ground oregano.
Brown lamb with marinade in oil.
When browned on all sides mix flour and add wine and garlic.
Add beef stock and vegetables (not pearl onions).
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add tomato paste for color and texture.
Add salt and pepper and basil to taste and the pearl onions.
Serve over rice.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Coat a glass baking dish with butter or margarine; place potato patties, side by side.
Mix all remaining ingredients, except 1 cup of grated cheese for topping.
Spread mixture over potato patties.
Top with remaining grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into well oiled baking dish. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes, covered.
Uncover and cook 5 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: smithart chocolate chip walnut pie
directions: Beat
eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix butter and cheese together. Add flour; blend well. Add Rice Krispies. Form into balls about the size of a walnut. Flatten with hands and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl and toss well. Combine yogurt and honey in a small bowl; whisk until well blended. Pour over apple mixture and toss gently. Sprinkle with pecans and Blue cheese (omit for a more kid friendly fruit salad).

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook and slice sausage.
Cook ziti according to directions on box.
Put all ingredients, except cheese, in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: banana pudding
directions: Stir sugar, flour and eggs together.
Add milk.
Cook over medium-high heat; stir constantly until thick.
Remove from heat. Put layer of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat until desired amount.

title: sherry apple pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Drain pan drippings.
Place chopped apples and onion on top of chops.
Combine sherry and next 4 ingredients.
Pour over chops.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until chops are tender.
Put chops on serving plate.

title: shoney's hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat until butter is melted and sauce is warm.
Do not boil!
Serve with brownies and vanilla ice cream.

title: petite sour cream balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350° about 15 minutes before baking time.
Mix all ingredients; spoon into petite muffin pans that have been greased.
The dough can be made and refrigerated 2 days before using.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all 3 ingredients. Form into balls. Roll in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with sugared fork. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown. Cool on rack. Enjoy with milk.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread as directed on package.
Put in refrigerator overnight or cool good.
Crumble cornbread.
Mix all ingredients real good.
Add enough Miracle Whip to hold together.
Don't use too much, not more than 3/4 cup.
Let set overnight.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients, but blueberries, in mixing bowl until blended.
Fold in berries.
Put in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: roll out cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs and add rest of the ingredients. Form into 5 round balls and chill several hours or overnight on a floured plate.
Roll out and use Christmas cookie cutters.
Bake. Ice and use any kind of sprinkles.

title: pumpkin pie *
directions: Turn on oven and set at 375°.
Mix brown sugar, flour, spice and salt in a 3-quart bowl.
Add pumpkin, milk and egg and stir until smooth.
Pour in unbaked shells.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm or cold.
Each serves 6.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine together and pat in pan. Blend cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar together for topping. Pour on top of crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot bars
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, oil, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Mix well and add carrots.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend sugars and shortening.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Mix flour, soda and salt; add to other mix.
Mix well.
Stir in M&M's. Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: barber poles
directions: Use bread sticks of your choice.
Wrap bacon strip around the bread and broil until done.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Cook hen until tender, removing from broth and debone for serving.
Make up dumplings using flour, salt, egg and enough broth to make dough consistency.

Knead until it holds in a ball. Roll dough thin and cut in strips. Break off into small pieces and drop in boiling broth. Turn down heat while you roll another batch. Continue until all flour mixture is used.
Shake pot periodically (never stir).
Cover and turn to simmer for about 10 minutes.
(Can substitute larger fryer for hen.)

title: apple raisin snack cake
directions: Measure all ingredients into large mixing bowl. Blend at low speed 1 minute. Scrape down and blend 1/2 minute longer. Beat for 2 1/2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into well-greased pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center springs back when touched lightly with finger.
Dust with powdered sugar or put icing on, if desired.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix and pour into greased muffin pan. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: sourdough banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Place all dry ingredients in at once.
Put into a well greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Place on a turned over pie pan placed in a 14-inch Dutch oven. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for about 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 9-inch pie.

title: brown rice
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in oven at 450° for 35 minutes.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in cocoa and flour. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto hot waffle iron. Bake for about 50 seconds. Remove with fork and frost with chocolate frosting recipe.

title: mrs. swift's pineapple cheese cake
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to custard.
Put gelatine in water; pour into custard and cook (jell).
Beat egg whites until stiff and dry.
Beat cream; add vanilla.
Add cottage cheese to jell mix; fold in whipped cream and egg whites.
Add pineapple.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: polish sausage
directions: Mix and roll into 2 or 3 rolls.
Wrap in foil (shiny side in). Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Punch holes in bottom of foil with fork.
Place in deep pan and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
tags: Morton Tender Quick meat cure salt

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Stir all together.
Alternate with cheese in greased pan; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan-cinnamon buns
directions: Mix 2 packages yeast in 1 cup warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Mix flour, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Put shortening in and add egg.
Add 1 cup milk to yeast mixture and pour into flour mixture.
Knead dough and let it rise for an hour.
Knead down and cover for second hour.
Separate dough in 3 pieces.
Roll out about 18-inches long and 9-inches wide.
Spread with margarine.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Roll longwise and cut into 1-inch slices.
Bake 25 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Brown chicken lightly in oil.
Add water, wine, broccoli and soup.
Bring to a boil, separating broccoli pieces.
Stir in rice. Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place mixture in pan and let set 1/4 hour.
Brush chicken pieces with oleo.
Place on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: crab-chokes
directions: Take raw fresh artichokes and wash and core centers.
Break middle and remove, leaving cup like artichoke.
Set aside.
Mix together thoroughly the shredded crab, diced onion and the cheese. Mix to consistency with mayonnaise.
Add salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and garlic salt to taste.
Mix well to consistency of salad dressing.
Stuff center of artichokes with mixture.
Set in deep baking dish.
Fill 1/2 of the way with water.
Cover and bake for 1 hour or until tender.
Remove and serve; pull hot leaves off and dip in melted center.
Enjoy.

title: chili con queso
directions: Peel, seed and chop tomatoes. Finely chop onions.
Saute butter and onions. Add tomatoes and chili.
Cook approximately 10 minutes (until well blended). Cut cream cheese in small pieces. Add to tomato and onion mixture.
Stir and cook together.
When cheese begins to melt, add heavy cream.
Cook until thick.
(Stir to prevent sticking.)
Place in heated chafing dish. Serve with Doritos.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind hot pepper (de-seeded) and bell pepper.
Mix peppers, vinegar and sugar.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool 3 to 5 minutes.
Add Certo and stir well.
Pour into sterilized pint jars and seal. Yield:
3 pints.

title: noodle chicken
directions: Arrange the cut up chicken in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with flour and pepper.
Mix the mushroom soup, milk and onion soup mix.
Pour over the chicken and sprinkle with the chow mein noodles.
Bake until chicken is tender when tested with a fork, about 1 hour.
Baking temperature is 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients and simmer 2 hours.

title: orange carrot cookies
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix grated rind, orange juice and powdered sugar to make frosting.
Frost cookies while they are warm.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: hot holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
When juices are thawed, place pan on medium heat.
Do not boil.
After 5 minutes, turn heat to low.
Hold for 25 minutes to allow flavors to blend. Strain before serving.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: lentils
directions: Wash lentils and soak overnight.
Place in a large pan, adding 4 pints of hot water.
Simmer until the lentils begin to soften, stirring from time to time.
When the lentils are half-cooked, add the chopped onions and continue to simmer until the lentils are quite tender.

title: banana split cake
directions: Pack the first 2 ingredients in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lo-cal quick chicken dumplings
directions: Place in a large boiler, the broth, soup and water.
Stir and mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to keep hot until ready to add to dumplings.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix all ingredients really well.
Add 3 cups cold water.
Put into ice molds or trays.
Freeze.

title: deep dish chocolate pie
directions: Scald milk.
Mix the next 4 ingredients well.
Add to milk. Cook on low heat, stirring constantly.
Add well beaten egg yolks. Slowly cook until thickened.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Stir and cool.
Pour into baked pie shell in deep, rectangular baking dish. Top with meringue.
Yields two deep dish pie shells.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion; drain.
Put in crock-pot with other ingredients.
Cook for
1 hour or until done.

title: crab dip
directions: Layer #1:
Combine cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and onion.
Spread on bottom of large oval platter or round rimmed plate dish.

title: yummy dessert
directions: Beat pudding and milk, then add Cool Whip.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan on sides and bottom.
Line bottom of pan with crackers. Pour 1/2 mixture on crackers, then another layer of crackers, then the remaining mixture, then another layer of crackers.
On the top, put icing.

title: granny's spice cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg, corn syrup, orange peel and cold water.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves; add to creamed mixture and mix well. Chill for at least 1 hour.
On a lightly floured surface, roll dough, a portion at a time, to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Decorate as desired.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Yields about 4 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Soak yeast in warm water a few minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar. Combine
mashed potatoes, white sugar, soft margarine, salt
and shortening.
Add a little flour before you add yeast mixture.
Add yeast
and
cool
potato
water.
Add
eggs and enough flour to make dough soft; knead.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Warm
and grease bowl you plan to let dough rise in. Flip dough
over
so it will be greasy.
Punch down and spread in
pie pans, well-greased.
Let rise until double in bulk. Sprinkle
cinnamon, melted
butter and brown sugar over cake. Punch
holes
into
cake with
fingers.
Bake
at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually and beat until thick.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Make 1 gallon.

title: homemade rice-a-roni
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add rice.
Break up raw spaghetti into 1/2 to 1-inch pieces.
Cook in butter until golden brown. Add dry ingredients from soup mix and whatever amount of water suggested on box.
Simmer until water is absorbed.
Serves 6.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Combine ingredients (except olives).
Drain olives.
Roll cheese mixture in small bowl, covering a stuffed olive.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: cinnamon apple bake
directions: Spread apples in lightly greased 13x9 inch baking pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Top evenly with dry cake mix.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden and bubbly.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Add cream cheese mixture and mix well. Freeze overnight.
(Will keep for 3 months.) Partially thaw to serve.

title: liver pate
directions: Blend cream cheese and liver pate together.
Melt red madrilene and gelatin together; add a few drops of red coloring. Oil a mold or 2 small ones.
Pour a little madrilene mixture into mold and let set.
Add pate mixture and keep in center.
Pour remaining madrilene over and around; chill.
Keeps well; do not freeze.
Good for cocktail party, served with plain crackers.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Mix together and pour over top.

title: "red top" salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in pan of hot water.
Add lemon jello.
Add Philadelphia cream cheese; beat smooth and cool.
Mix in whipped cream and salad dressing.
Add crushed pineapple, drained.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients in a med. bowl.
Combine cracker crumbs and cheese in a shallow bowl.
Dip chicken in butter mixture;
dredge in cracker crumb mixture.
Place on a foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees for 25 - 30 min or until chicken is brown and done.
Delicious!

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick melted margarine and crumbs.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (press crumbs firm).
Beat with electric mixer the eggs, margarine and powdered sugar for 15 minutes.
Spread mixture over crust.
Place bananas, then drained pineapple on top of mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts and arrange cherries on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 15 to 18.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Add butter, sugar, milk, salt, orange rind and nuts to sweet potatoes; mix well.
Shape sweet potato mixture around each marshmallow.
Roll each ball in cornflakes.
Place on buttered baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Freeze until needed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix melted margarine and stuffing.
Make a crust with half of this mixture.
Combine all the other ingredients.
Top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix with 1 cup milk as directed on package. Fold in whipped topping. Stir 1 cup cookies and the rocks into the pudding mixture. Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies. Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Garnish with gumdrops, flowers or gummy worms, if desired.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.
Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: lemon dream pie
directions: Prepare topping as directed on package.
Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water.
Add ice cubes and stir constantly until gelatin is thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Blend whipped topping into Jell-O; whip until smooth.
Spoon into pie shell; chill 2 hours.
Garnish with lemon slices, if desired.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Pour juices into 8-cup automatic electric percolator.
Add sufficient water.
In percolator basket, put salt, spices and brown sugar.
Allow to perk 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve in mugs or punch cups.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: homemade cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pie filling) in a large bowl. Pour into large greased pan.
On top of mixture, pour the pie filling.
Pie filling can be substituted by 3 to 4 cups diced fresh fruit.
Keep berries away from sides of pan or they will stick.
Bake at 375° until batter is done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Wash
strawberries,
making
sure
they
don't stand in water. Cap
and
cut
away bruised spots.
Measure out 4 cups strawberries,
pile measure high.
Place strawberries in large saucepan
with
tight-fitting
lid.
Add 1 tablespoon vinegar. Put on
top
and
boil 1 minute by the clock.
Start timing it when the
boil
begins.
At the end of the minute, uncover and add 4 cups
sugar.
Stir
gently so the sugar and berries are blended. Cook
20 minutes at boiling point.
Pour into a bowl or shallow pan
or
meat
dish.
Let stand overnight or until cool. Pack
in clean jars; paraffin and seal or process in hot water bath 5 minutes.

title: pistachio-banana pie
directions: Mix milk, pudding, vanilla, and whip- Beat until stiff. Put 1/2 of mix in oreo shell. Slice bananas on top of mix. Add other 1/2 of filling over bananas. Make sure they cover all bananas. Chill about 3 hours.

title: squash dressing
directions: Bake cornbread and let cool; crumble.
Dice squash and chop onion; cook in margarine until tender.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: chicken with wine
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: annie's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly.
Spread on bottom of pie crust, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Cook puddings and milk and pour over crumbs.
When cool, spread top with Cool Whip and sprinkle reserved crumbs over.
This is delicious!

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, taco seasoning mix and milk until smooth.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan, then layer kind of thick with vegetables.
You can use any vegetables you prefer.

title: poor man's hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion, meat and garlic.
Drain well.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat through. Garnish with fresh parsley.
Serve over poppy seed noodles or cooked fluffy rice.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Fry sausage; remove grease.
Add vegetables and seasonings. Cook until tender.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and cocoa. Add milk in saucepan and bring to a boil for approximately 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, rolled oats and vanilla. Beat together until it loses its shine and spoon onto waxed paper.

title: rolls
directions: Scald milk and let cool to lukewarm.
Cream shortening and sugar, then add egg.
Mix well.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water. Pour yeast mixture and lukewarm milk into bowl with other ingredients; mix well.
Add 2 cups flour and mix; continue adding the flour 2 cups at a time, until all of the flour has been added to the mixture.

title: chef tell's braised brussels sprouts
directions: Cook sprouts in boiling salted water for 12 to 15 minutes. Rinse in cold water and set aside.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Boil 30-45 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Add the rest of the ingredients. (You may grate one of the potatoes to thicken soup.)
Bring to a boil again.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour.
The longer it simmers, the better it is!

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter, oil and marshmallows.
Pour over popcorn, gumdrops and nuts.
Mix and press into 2 (9 x 13-inch) buttered pans or angel food cake pan.
I use Spicettes or Spice Drops and peanuts.

title: robin's beefy onion gravy
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine broth, water, soup mix and pepper.
Heat to boiling on medium heat.
In a separate cup, stir flour and milk until smooth. Gradually stir into broth mixture. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to low. Cook 5 minutes.
Serve over beef.
Makes 3 cups.

title: copper carrots
directions: Slice carrots and cook in water until tender, drain.
Remove carrots, set aside and keep warm.
In the same saucepan;
combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and ginger.
Gradually stir in orange juice;
bring to a boil.
Cook and stir 2 minutes, add butter, return carrots to pan;
heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Place first 5 ingredients into a heavy frying pan.
Cook on stove.
Stir and cook for 10 minutes.
Should be gooey when done. Remove from stove and stir in Rice Krispies.
Use extra if sticky. Put coconut on waxed paper.
Drop cookie mixture by teaspoon onto coconut and roll.

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Saute scallions and garlic in margarine until softened.
Add crabmeat, vermouth and lemon juice until heated throughout.
Transfer to mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients, except mushrooms and cheese.
Mix well.
Fill mushroom caps and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake until mushrooms are tender, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, then add coconut and chopped nuts.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan at 350° about 35 minutes. While hot, pour marshmallow cream over and let cool.

title: red rice
directions: Saute onion in butter.
When onion begins to wilt or cook, add rice to frying
pan.
Stir rice and onion 3 minutes.
The rice should be thoroughly coated with butter.
Transfer rice mix to a saucepan.
Add bouillon, onion, salt and tomato sauce.
Stir. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat.
Cover
pot and cook over very low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fish casserole
directions: Boil fish in salted water until done.
Melt Velveeta, milk and shrimp soup until smooth.
Mix in fish.
Put in casserole dish; top with crumbs.
Keep warm in oven.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix rice and broccoli.
Combine cheese and mushroom soup and mix well.
Then add celery.
Spread into a 9-inch buttered square pan and bake for 30 minutes.

title: tomato-rice soup
directions: Combine and simmer on low for 15 minutes.

title: noodle chili(serves 8)
directions: Saute onion, celery and burger.
Combine all ingredients. Heat.

title: john's firecracker sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with taco chips.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans in bottom of a greased tube pan; set aside. Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters or halves; roll each piece in sugar mixture and layer in pan.
Combine brown sugar and margarine.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan and put on serving platter.

title: upside-down cake(no fat, no cholesterol)
directions: Combine first four ingredients and put into a 9 x 11-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Combine dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites, skim milk, syrup and vanilla together, just to combine.
Add dry ingredients.
Carefully pour over fruit mixture and smooth over.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 48 minutes.
Invert onto plate or platter, if desired.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix with mixer.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or golden.
Serve with crackers.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Alternate buttermilk with dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes in 10-inch iron skillet or 2-quart Pyrex dish.

title: blueberry cream supreme jello salad
directions: Mix jello in hot water.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Put 1/2 in pan and chill until firmly set.
Leave rest at room temperature.
When chilled, spread with mixture of sour cream, vanilla, sugar and mayonnaise.
Chill 15 minutes.
Cover with remaining jello mixture and chill until set.

title: brown rice
directions: Cut onion into melted butter and brown well over medium heat. Pour into baking dish. Add rice and bouillon. Cover with top and bake 1 hour at 350°. Stir once at end of first 30 minutes.

title: carla's apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in greased baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle with cinnamon and water.
Work together sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: dill kosher pickles
directions: Heat sugar,
vinegar, water and celery seed to boiling. Pour over sliced (long way) pickles and onion in jar.
Let set for a couple of days in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix lightly with a fork the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
In another bowl, beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients. Stir well.
Add zucchini and chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° in greased loaf pans (2) until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar to boiling.
Mix the vegetables well and pour vinegar mixture over them.
Chill overnight.

title: havarti's black bean-corn salad
directions: Combine black beans, corn, tomatoes, bell pepper, red onion and parsley into a large bowl. Add salad dressing and toss to mix well. Chill, covered, until ready to serve. Top with cheese cubes. Makes 4 to 6 servings. Best with Italian dressing.

title: fat-free carrot cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking soda and cinnamon and stir to mix well.
Stir in the orange juice, egg substitute and vanilla extract.
Fold in the carrots and raisins or walnuts, if desired.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread the batter evenly in the pan and bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes or just until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature.

title: french dressing
directions: In a bowl or jar, mix vinegar, sugar and onion.
Comine salt, mustard, paprika and two tablespoons chili sauce to form a paste. Add remaining chili sauce and mix well.
Pour into vinegar mixture, add oil and mix or shake well.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together graham crackers and margarine in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; set aside. Cream together in mixer cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and Milnot.
Add jello and mix together.
Pour into cracker crust. Chill.

title: candied yams
directions: Spray a shallow baking dish with nonstick coating. Cut larger pieces of yam in half.
Place in the dish in a single layer. In a saucepan, melt margarine, cinnamon and brown sugar. Add 1/3 package marshmallows and mix well to melt.
Pour marshmallow mixture over yams.
Sprinkle more marshmallows on top. Bake for 45 minutes at 325°, basting often.

title: jimmy's corn casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, over medium heat, melt the last 5 ingredients.
Add corn to the cream cheese mixture and stir. Grease a casserole and pour in the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lime gelatin mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water, stirring well.
Put in refrigerator until it starts to set, then add pineapple, lemon juice and salad dressing.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put into mold and chill until firm.
Nuts can also be added.

title: homemade sour cream
directions: Mix and let it stand in warm place overnight or until thickened.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Place corned beef in large stew pot and cover with water.
Boil for 2 to 3 hours, until fork-tender.
Remove from the pot; save water.
Place potatoes, carrots, onions and turnip in pot and boil for 1/2 hour.
Add cabbage and boil for another 15 minutes.
Slice beef in diagonal slices against the grain.
Arrange all on a platter and serve with Mustard Sauce and Irish soda bread.

title: pork and bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: face paint
directions: In each cup of the muffin tin, mix cornstarch, water, cold cream and a couple drops of food coloring (a different color for each one).
Stir.

title: fried zucchini cakes
directions: Mix together the buttermilk baking mix, cheese, salt and pepper. Stir in eggs until mixture just becomes moist. Fold in the zucchini. Melt the oleo in a 10-inch skillet over moderate heat. Use 2 tablespoons batter for each zucchini cake. Fry zucchini cakes for about 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until brown. Makes 8 to 10 cakes.

title: seafood cheese ball
directions: Combine all and shape into ball or shape into log.
Roll in chopped nuts or sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Chill.

title: bread and cheese souffle
directions: Place buttered bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan 2 layers deep.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over bread.
Beat eggs and milk and pour over cheese and bread.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 persons.

title: quick brownies
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs and oil.
Add melted chocolate or cocoa, flour, salt and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in shallow pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Saute onion, green chiles and garlic in oil.
Reduce heat to low and add remaining ingredients, except tomato juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Add tomato juice gradually, until dip is the desired consistency.
Place over hot water to keep warm.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes 3 1/4 cups of dip.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and melted margarine together and beat well. Add flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well. Add sugar mixture. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hunters pie
directions: Cook vegetables in water until tender. Drain, reserving 1 1/2 c. liquid; set aside.

title: cheddar puffs
directions: Cream margarine with cheese until smooth in a medium size bowl.
Blend in flour, salt and paprika, then knead lightly with hands to form a soft dough.

title: tourtiere(french meat pie)
directions: *Spices may be added while cooking or preferably after meat/onion have been cooked.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Combine sauce ingredients.
Mix well.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Arrange chicken in single layer.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Any seafood seasoning may be substituted for the Cajun.

title: cream puffs
directions: In 2 qt saucepan bring water to boil.
Add butter and melt. Add flour and salt all at once and stir until mixture leaves side of pan.
Remove from heat and add eggs one at a time beating thoroughly after each addition.
Drop dough by scant 1/4 cupfuls on baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 400 F oven for 40-45 minutes.

title: sparerib sauce
directions: To make as a barbecue sauce, decrease the water to 3/4 cup and boil down to thickness desired.
Bake ribs at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pinch off and roll in coconut.
Chill.
Makes about 50 balls.
Keep refrigerated.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crumble taco chips in bottom of casserole (about 1/3 package). Add hamburger, browned and drained, cooked with chili powder, Mexican chili beans and chili without beans.
Mix all together and pour over taco chips.
Add grated cheese on top.
Crumble rest of taco chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve on shredded lettuce, tomatoes and taco sauce.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend 1 minute on low speed in mixer bowl.
Add 48 eggs; blend 30 seconds.
Add 3 quarts oil; beat 6 minutes.
Add 2 gallons and 1 quart shredded carrots and 1 1/2 (#10) cans crushed pineapple. Blend 30 seconds and beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Put this
mixture
in
a tray of sifted plain flour and mix with
hands
until	stiff
enough to roll out on a floured board. Roll
to
medium thickness, cut with a knife or cookie cutter and bake in a moderate oven until brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil Mueller's until tender.
Rinse with cold water; drain. Cool.
Put in a bowl.
Pour dressing in, stirring occasionally. Store in refrigerator overnight.
Just before serving, put in tomatoes, cut small, and the cheese, cut up fine.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat together with mixer and spread in pan.

title: rocky road candy
directions: On low heat, melt together milk, chocolate chips and butter. Pour into bowl with peanuts and marshmallows.
Blend well.
Pour into 9 x 11-inch pan; refrigerate.
Cut into squares and serve. If bottom of pan is lined with wax paper candy is easier to remove.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 250 degrees.
Cream together brown sugar, butter, eggs and milk.
Sift baking soda, 2 cups flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, and cloves together.
Combine dry mixture and creamy mixture.
Add water.
Coat fruit with remaining cup of flour. Stir coated fruit and pecan pieces into dough.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Cook slowly, approximately 12 - 15 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: savory meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding chips last.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Remove stem ends from tomatoes.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/2-inch walls.
Chop pulp; mix with remaining ingredients. Fill tomatoes with stuffing.
Arrange in a circle in 9-inch pie dish.
Cover loosely and cook on High for 3 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn; cook until hot, 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Garnish with parsley if desired.

title: p-nutty muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place paper liners in muffin tins.
Set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg in a medium bowl.
Toss with a fork to blend; set aside.
Peel banana; break into small pieces and set aside on wax paper.
In a large mixing bowl combine peanut butter and sugar.
Mix at medium speed to blend, scraping sides of bowl with a rubber spatula, if necessary.
Add eggs; blend.
Add bananas; blend.
Add flour mixture in 2 stages and mix until completely blended in.
Do not overmix.
Add sour cream; blend.
Spoon batter into muffin cups to 3/4 full.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
If preparing for freezer, cool completely and then wrap in plastic wrap and freeze.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add all remaining ingredients and stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: mom's sunday pot roast
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Dust lightly with flour and brown both sides in hot oiled skillet.
Reduce heat to low and add sliced onion directly on top of meat and add peeled and cut up potatoes and carrots on top and around meat.
Add about 1/2 cup water.
Cover tightly and go to church.
Three hours later, you've got an entire meal.
You may add a green salad and some hot rolls, and if you're lucky some of Mom's green beans and you've got a feast.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mash avocados.
Add salt, pepper and lemon juice; set aside. Mix taco seasoning with sour cream and set aside.
Spread in center of large shallow plate leaving 1-inch around the plate. Layer the following ingredients in order listed; avocado mixture, onion, tomatoes and black olives.
Top with cheese.
Arrange chips around the plate edge.

title: carrot-top souffle
directions: Bring the carrots, cut in half, with water to cover to a boil in large saucepan. Reduce heat to medium and cook carrots 30 minutes until very tender; drain.

title: microwave nut crunch
directions: Roast nuts by placing in a single layer on a baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until just beginning to turn brown. Mix together sugar, cinnamon, salt and milk; microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir, then microwave again for 1 minute or until thickened. Stir in vanilla and nuts, coating well. Spoon onto wax paper, separating nuts slightly so they don't clump. Allow to cool. Makes 10 (1/4 cup) servings.

title: turkey and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook noodles and broccoli as directed on packages, then drain. Melt margarine in medium size pot; slowly stir in flour and seasonings. Add milk slowly to mixture while cooking on low and stirring constantly until thickened. Remove from heat. Add cheese and stir until melted. Place noodles, broccoli and turkey in a baking dish.
