Bake uncovered at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs, milk, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg in a shallow bowl.
Dip slices of bread into the mixture, then fry, using bacon grease or a spray.
When golden brown on both sides, serve. Should make 8 slices.
Serve with syrup, honey or preserves.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla in bowl.
Blend. Combine pumpkin and milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture alternately with pumpkin mixture.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake in greased and lightly floured bread pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bubble and squeak
directions: Melt the butter in a large frying pan. Add the onion and cook for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until softened.
Add the potatoes, cabbage and beef. Season to taste. Fry over medium heat for about 15 minutes, stirring frequently, until browned. Serve hot.

title: snowballs
directions: Melt butter and add sugar, flour, vanilla and then nuts. Roll into small balls. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly brown. While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar. After completely cooled, roll again in confectioners sugar. Yield: 90 to 100 cookies.

title: pizza pinwheel appetizers
directions: Separate dough into four rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spread each rectangle with 1 tablespoon of pizza sauce. Sprinkle with 1 ounce Mozzarella cheese and 1 1/2 ounces pepperoni, pressing lightly.
Roll up, starting at short end.
Seal edges.

title: date balls
directions: Let cool; roll in small balls and dust with powdered sugar.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup milk.
Blend until smooth.
Add remaining milk.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Cook until thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut. Cover for 5 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake.

title: french green salad
directions: Whisk lemon juice and mustard together in a salad bowl.
Whisk in chicken stock, oil and garlic.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Wash romaine lettuce.
Tear into bite size pieces and add to bowl. Wipe endive with a damp paper towel.
Slice into pieces and add to bowl.
Toss well.
Makes 2 servings.

title: bacon stuffed burgers
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and discard all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Saute onions in drippings until tender. Crumble bacon; add mushrooms to skillet and set aside.

title: cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower according to instructions and drain well. In a casserole, combine cauliflower, soup, Worcestershire sauce and cheese.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Melt
butter
in
soup	kettle.
Add
coarsely	chopped onion. Cook until
limp
but not brown.
Add the ground beef; stir until meat
is
not
red.
Pour in tomatoes, consomme and water.	Add celery tops, parsley, thyme, peppercorns and salt. Cover and cook over a very low heat for about 45 minutes.

title: sparkling raspberry cooler
directions: In a 2-quart nonmetal pitcher, combine juice concentrate and sparkling water.
Stir to blend.
Serve over ice cubes or crushed ice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: citrus salad
directions: Slice oranges; take pith out and discard white.
Squeeze lemon, remove seed.
Retain pulp.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: quick and easy fudge(microwave)
directions: Line bottom of an 8-inch square baking pan with waxed paper; set aside.
Combine first 6 ingredients in a 2-quart casserole, stirring gently.
Add butter; microwave, uncovered, at High for 2 or 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Refrigerate until firm; cut into squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: brown edge cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar first. Add one egg at a time until blended. Add flour gradually while mixing.

title: mississippi fudge cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a bowl.
In saucepan, combine oleo, water and cocoa; beat until boiling.
Add while hot to sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients; beat well.
Pour into large, prepared sheet cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 pecan loaf
directions: One Bowl Method:
Cream shortening with sugar; add dry ingredients, alternately, with remaining ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: captain crunch cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler.
Pour over mixture of remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper.

title: heavenly chicken
directions: In small saucepan, cook spinach according to package; drain well.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Stir together dressing, wine and seasonings.
Pour mix over chicken.
Cover; refrigerate several hours.
Drain, reserving dressing mix.
Place chicken on greased rack of broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 6 minutes on each side or until tender, brushing frequently with dressing.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Cool.
Whip mayonnaise and cream cheese together.
Add whipped cream.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Garnish with green grapes and fresh parsley.
Chill. Serves 8.

title: corn casserole 2
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first four ingredients in large bowl, mix well.
Add onion, bell pepper and melted margarine. Pour mixture into lightly greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix Cheddar cheese and sour cream and spoon over mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Slice potatoes (peeled or unpeeled).
In casserole dish, place in layers the potatoes, meat and onions.
Pour soup over all and bake until potatoes are done, about 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle cheese on top and put back in oven until it melts.

title: potato sausage casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, onions and seasonings.
Layer sausage, potatoes and soup mix.
Dot each layer with butter.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tom's favorite chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add milk and egg yolks. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla; cool slightly.
Add to baked pie shell; top with meringue and brown.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger
and
onion;
add remaining ingredients. Heat and
add cheese.
When cheese melts, it's ready to serve. Good with Fritos dip chips.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Flake chicken into casserole dish. Combine milk and soup and pour over chicken.
Melt butter.
Add to broth, then combine with dressing.
Spoon this mixture over chicken.
Please note:
You may use cream of celery soup and 24 crushed Ritz crackers instead of chicken soup and dressing.
This is just as good.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: eggplant
directions: Put eggplant in dish and add Parmesan cheese and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Put oil and cold water in cup; don't stir.
Add all at once to flour; stir lightly and form with hands.

title: danish puff
directions: Mix first three ingredients with fork.
Roll into ball and divide in half.
Pat dough with hands into 2 strips (12 x 13-inch). Place on cookie sheet.
Mix 1/2 of margarine and 1 cup water in pan and bring to a boil.
Add almond flavoring and remove from heat. Stir in flour immediately to keep it from lumping.
When smooth and thick, add eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth.
Divide in half and spread evenly over each piece of pastry.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Frost with powdered sugar icing flavored with almond extract when cool.

title: stir-fry chicken and broccoli
directions: Place chicken, cornstarch and soy sauce in a bowl; stir until chicken is thoroughly coated.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Heat oil in wok over high heat.
Add chicken and stir-fry until browned. Remove chicken from wok.
Add broccoli and onion to wok; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms and bean sprouts.
Return chicken to pan.
Stir in chicken broth; cover and cook gently for 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken n' dumplins
directions: Pa gits* me a big fat plum hen.
After she's been kilt* , clean her up real good by pluckin* all the feathers off'n her.
Senge* the pin feathers off'n her by holding her over a paper poke* that's been set a far* . Then worsh* her real good.
Cut her up and put in a kettle of water with salt and pepper.
Bil* until tender.
Add dumplins* by pinching off and cook til they git* hard.
(P.S.
Use dumplin* recipe.)

title: gooey butter bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together cream cheese, eggs, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Place on top of bottom layer.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle baked bars with powdered sugar and cut into bars when cool.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix pie filling as directions on box.
Add peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: candied sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Slice potatoes into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place on bottom of a shallow, 2-quart glass baking dish.
Layer sliced apples over potatoes; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nutmeg. Cook, covered, in microwave oven on High for 4 minutes or until heated through.

title: sensational beef stroganoff
directions: Cook 1/2 the beef and 1/2 the onion in 1 tablespoon margarine until beef is no longer pink and onion is tender; set aside. Repeat with remaining margarine, beef and onion.
Return meat mixture to skillet.
Stir in soup and paprika.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to very low.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together.
Place bacon on top and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: creamy broccoli
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
In a separate saucepan, put margarine, shredded cheese and 1/2 cup milk.
Stir with fork constantly until smooth.
Add more milk if you desire a thinner sauce.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli.
Sprinkle with sunflower seeds, salt and pepper to taste.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle beef brisket generously with garlic salt, onion salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour liquid smoke over meat and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and cream of tartar.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Chop potatoes into bite size pieces; chop onion too.
Put chopped onion and potatoes on a large piece of heavy duty aluminum foil.
Add butter, salt, pepper and water.
Seal tightly and place on hot grill approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn occasionally.
Great when topped with Ranch dressing.

title: texas bar and grill sauce
directions: Puree jalapenos and onions in blender or food processor. Place mixture in mixer bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat on low speed for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 cups.

title: creamy cocoa mix
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir well.
Store in a Ziploc plastic bag.

title: conestoga rolls
directions: Mix yeast and hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Beat egg and add to yeast mixture.
Add soft oleo, then add sugar and flour. Seal in container.
Let sit in refrigerator about 2 hours.
Spray muffin pan with cooking spray.
Spoon 1 tablespoon for each roll. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Keeps up to 1 week in refrigerator.
Makes about 18 rolls.

title: great burgers
directions: Mix well and shape into burgers; fry.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes last and pour into greased casserole dish.
Place topping on top of the potato mixture and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
(This recipe freezes well.)

title: robert's oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugars with electric mixer. Add egg and vanilla. Beat well. Add combined flour, baking soda and cinnamon. Stir in oats and raisins. Allow a few minutes to hydrate. Stir in broken pecans. Spray hands with Pam. Form cookies. Spray cookie sheet with Pam and place cookies on sheet. Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes or not quite done. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Transfer to wire rack. Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: barbecued pot roast
directions: Brown pot roast in lard.
Pour off drippings.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add to pot roast.
Cover tightly; simmer 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Thicken liquid for gravy.

title: spicy nut triangles
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Grease tube pan, 10 x 4-inches or 12-cup Bundt cake pan. Prepare one of the fillings; reserve. Beat sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs in a 2 1/2-quart bowl on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 2 minutes. Beat in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt alternately with sour cream on low speed. Spread 1/3 of the batter (about 2 cups) in pan. Sprinkle with 1/3 of the filling. Repeat 2 times. Bake until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean, about 1 hour. Cool 20 minutes. Remove from pan; drizzle with Glaze.

title: pancakes
directions: Make your favorite pancake recipe.
Cook eggs soft or hard. Put 1 pancake on plate, then egg, then pancake on top with peanut butter and hot syrup.
Just like grandpa used to eat.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add soda to flour.
Add alternately flour and sour cream to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in.
Bake in large size tube pan, greased and floured, at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Should have nice brown crust on top.
Let stand 15 minutes before taking out of pan.

title: best ever picnic ham
directions: Score the picnic ham on top and put fresh garlic cloves in the scoring.
Pour the spicy mustard over the ham.
Bake at 325° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: sweet potato puddin
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
Grate or put in food processor set for coarse.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Add sugar, eggs, nutmeg, vanilla flavoring and orange juice. Baked in a glass pan or your favorite baking pan, 1/2 hour, then add margarine.
Cook about 1 hour at 375° or until potatoes are done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Place in ungreased casserole dish.
Place in preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together on medium heat. When well blended, add rest of ingredients. Mix well, being careful not to crush Rice Krispies. While still hot, make into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: sadie's dilly bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Meanwhile heat cottage cheese and butter until butter is just melted - only luke warm.
Combine sugar, onion, dill weed, salt and baking soda in a large bowl. Add cottage cheese and butter; mix well.
Add egg; mix well.
Add yeast mixture; mix well.
Slowly add flour; mix well.

title: 1922 biscuits for two
directions: Mix as usual, making a soft dough.
Roll and cut in biscuit shape.
Bake in hot oven.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: cheerios nutty crunch
directions: Cook sugar, butter and corn syrup until bubbly, then cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in salt and soda.
Stir until uniformly light in color.
Mix cereal, raisins and nuts.
Pour syrup over all and mix well.
Spread mixture evenly in large greased pan and bake at 250° for 15 minutes.

title: diet perch
directions: Remove skin from fillets and cut into serving-size portions. Place fish in a single layer in a shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over fish.
Let stand for 30 minutes, turning once.
Remove fish, reserving sauce for basting. Place fish on well-greased broiler pan.
Broil about 4 minutes. Turn carefully and baste with sauce.
Broil approximately 4 more minutes.

title: golden caramel popcorn
directions: Pop the popcorn as directed, omitting butter and salt.
Pour into large, greased baking pan.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to boil; boil 5 minutes, without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour syrup over corn, tossing to coat evenly.
Heat in 250° oven for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool corn.
It becomes crisp.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring pineapple and juice to a boil.
Remove from the heat and add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Cool to room temperature.
When begins to thicken slightly, fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Pour into 11 x 7 x 2-inch deep dish.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: sangria
directions: Into large pitcher, pour lemon juice, orange juice, and sugar; stir to dissolve sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
(I substitute the brandy for peach schnapps.)

title: german chocolate caramel bars
directions: Melt and stir caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in heavy pan.
Mix in large bowl the cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and pecans.
Stir until dough hangs together.
Press half of dough in well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over crust.
Pour caramel mix over chips.
Spoon rest of dough on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into bars.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Toss with the mayonnaise, mixed with sugar and vinegar.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Add to top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Cut up shrimp; toss with macaroni, cheese, celery, green pepper and onion.
Blend remaining ingredients; toss with shrimp mixture.
Cover.
Chill.
Before serving, stir salad.
If desired, serve in lettuce lined bowl and top with green pepper rings. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Bake pie crust until light brown.
Steam spinach, mushrooms and onion.
Drain well and set aside.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise, dill weed, basil and parsley.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Spread steamed vegetables into crust.
Pour egg mixture over top of vegetables. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey tetrazinni
directions: Boil turkey in a lot of water for broth.
Remove turkey and cook spaghetti in broth.
Drain and reserve some of the broth to dilute mushroom soup.
Cool chicken or turkey (helps if using boneless chicken).
Saute mushroom, peppers, pimento and celery in oil.
Dilute soup with lean broth (2 cups) and combine with meat, vegetables, cooked spaghetti, cheese and seasoning.
Place in 2 - 4 quart casseroles and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Freezes well. For low fat use fat free broth, no fat mushroom soup and light Velveeta cheese.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, bell pepper and onion into thin slices.
Put into large bowl or pan and sprinkle with salt.
Cover with ice water or ice and set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Bring to boil the sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Remove from heat and let cool.
When cooled, drain cucumbers and put into a gallon jug and pour the cooled liquid over the cucumbers and shake up.
Set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Ready to eat.
Will keep in refrigerator for 3 to 4 months.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown together ground beef, bacon and onion.
Drain grease off.
Add brown sugar and vinegar.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover the first 4 ingredients with ice water; let stand for 3 hours, then drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and let boil.
Pour over drained cucumbers and cook until heated well.
Put in jars and seal.

title: grandma meaney's crabmeat dip
directions: Mash softened cream cheese with a fork.
Add crabmeat and mix. Add mayonnaise, chili sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with a fork.
Add Tabasco to taste.
Chill overnight.
Serve with dip size Fritos.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, salt, pepper and garlic.
Add tomatoes and water, chili powder, oregano and bouillon cubes.
Add carrots and cabbage.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Add macaroni.
Cook until done.
Add beans and tomato sauce.
Heat.

title: beef and vegetable bake
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Put vegetables in a casserole dish. Add meat, then noodles and butter.
Bake about 20 minutes at 400° and top with cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: sweet and savory meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and egg.
Shape into 16 meatballs; brown and drain.
Combine golden mushroom soup, catsup, vinegar, brown sugar and soy sauce. Pour over meatballs.
Cover and cook in skillet on low temperature for 20 minutes, or bake in covered casserole at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mamaw's italian spaghetti
directions: Brown ground sirloin in cooking oil and drain carefully.
In large mixing bowl, mix the tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms and olives.
Saute onions and green peppers.
Add to the tomato mixture.
Add basil and oregano.
Simmer everything except the meat for 10 minutes, uncovered.
Add meat and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes longer.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line muffin tin with paper cups.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon equal amounts of mixture (about 3 tablespoons) into cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Chill.
Top with filling.

title: linguine with broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets off stems.
Cut stems into bite size pieces.
(Should make about 6 cups of stem pieces and flowerets.) Steam broccoli for about 5 minutes; drain.
In separate large pot, bring 4 quarts of water to a boil.
Cook linguine until cooked through; drain pasta.
Toss with broccoli.
Add oil, garlic and pepper to mixture.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: holiday pate
directions: Mix cream cheese and corned beef until well blended.
Add olives, onion, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Mix well and place in greased ring mold.
Chill.
Unmold and decorate with parsley and pimento to resemble a wreath.
Serve with crackers.

title: caramel layer cake squares
directions: Melt and set aside caramels and 1/3 cup canned milk.
Mix by hand the cake mix, margarine, 1/3 cup canned milk and nuts.
Press 1/2 dough in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle 1 cup chocolate chips. Spread caramels over chips.
Top with remaining dough.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar (mix well).
Put eggs in a separate bowl; beat for 2 minutes, or until well mixed.
Add eggs with butter and sugar mixture.
Beat until cake mixture is smooth (sugar grains well dissolved).
If cake mix is very smooth, add milk and beat momentarily.
Add 2 cups flour; mix well.
Add remainder of flour; beat until light.
Add flavor; beat 1 minute. Pour mixture into regular size baking pans; cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 pans.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Crumble shrimp and set aside.
Blend together
cream cheese and mayonnaise, then add shrimp.
Mix in celery, green onion and lemon juice.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet & sour kielbasa
directions: Place kielbasa in baking pan. Pour sweet and sour sauce over kielbasa. Sprinkle brown sugar on top. Bake at 350° for 30-40 min. or until bubbly. When done cut in slices and add a toothpick for easy eating.

title: brownie cookie
directions: Cream
together
the
margarine and sugar. Add the eggs and vanilla.
Cream
again and add the remaining ingredients. Chill 20	minutes.
Roll	into 1-inch balls and then into the confectioners
sugar.
Bake
at
for 11 minutes or until done.

title: 63 chevy zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 325° for one hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, but cheese and onions in casserole dish.
Top with cheese then onions.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate rocky road pudding
directions: Mix pudding and marshmallows; spoon into serving dishes. Garnish with whipped topping.

title: easy cookies
directions: Add brown sugar (can use same beater) to egg white.
Add chopped nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 300° oven (do not brown top; bottom may be lightly brown) for about 15 minutes.
Or heat oven to 375° and put cookies in for 1 minute.
Turn oven off.
Leave in oven several hours, if this latter method is used.
Place in a tight tin.
Best not made in rainy weather.

title: french ham and cheese souffle
directions: In a large baking dish (13 x 9-inch), place cubed bread. Combine flour and dry mustard.
Sprinkle 1/3 mustard mix over bread.
Dribble 1 tablespoon of the butter over bread.
Sprinkle ham over mixture in dish, covering as before with 1/3 of dry mixture and 1 tablespoon butter.
Lastly, put on cheese, remaining mustard mixture and butter.
Beat together eggs and milk.
Pour over dish mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cook ground beef and drain well. Mix all ingredients in crock pot and simmer until cheese is melted.

title: cream-cheese frosting
directions: In small bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese with milk just until smooth.
Gradually beat in vanilla, salt and sugar until blended.
Fills and frosts 2-layer cake, frosts a 13 x 9-inch cake, tube cake or 2 dozen cupcakes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix beans and bean juice.
Place mixture in casserole dish. Grill 3 onions.
Put on top of beans. Crush crackers and mix with soup.
Put on top of onions.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: seafood quiche
directions: *You can use Kemp water-packed crab and lobster (fake) meat (chunk-style).

title: no peek chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking pan.
Mix together other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°. "Don't peek!"

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; stir well.
This will make enough for 3 to 4 pounds of chicken.
Add chicken.
For wings, cut off small wing tips at joint and discard, then cut wing in half at the other joint.
Marinate for 2 hours or overnight.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into small balls.
Arrange in baking dish.

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Mix together meat, salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 patties. Place on greased grill over hot coals. Grill, uncovered, 10 minutes or to desired doneness, turning and brushing with sauce. Preparation time:
10 minutes. Cooking time: 10 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, 1/2 c. pecans, celery, green peppers, onion and seasoning salt until thoroughly blended.
Shape into 2 - 8 inch logs.
Roll in remaining pecans and chill.
Yields 2 - 8 inch logs.

title: poulet d'artichoke
directions: Cook artichokes per package, adding a little olive oil and garlic cloves.
Drain cooked artichokes and arrange in a greased baking dish or 8 individual ramekins.
Spread cooked chicken on top of artichokes (1/3 per ramekin).

title: roommate's rouladen
directions: Spread mustard over beaten steak.
Cover with bacon and add a row of pickles.
Start rolling up lengthwise.
Pin with toothpicks.
Roll in flour and brown.
Place in pan and cover with onion soup mix.
Cook at 250° with a small amount of water added to pan for about 2 to 3 hours or until steak is tender.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Layer broccoli and chicken.
Mix together next five ingredients.
Pour over chicken and broccoli. Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: sherry cake
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix at low speed for 1 minute, then at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Flour and grease a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool on rack; dust with powdered sugar.

title: julie's roast
directions: Saute onions and oleo.
When tender, add bread.
Put into large bowl and add Vegeburger, garlic salt, cheese, eggs and poultry seasoning.
Mix well and bake in pan which has ketchup mixed with brown sugar in bottom.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°. Failproof and delicious.

title: hawaiian fruit compote
directions: Combine pineapple chunks, tangerines, banana, strawberries, orange juice concentrate and soda in a large bowl; toss gently. Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Makes about 16 half-cup servings.
Each serving is 53 calories.

title: vidalia onions with balsamic vinegar
directions: Cut onions into wedges. Combine all ingredients and pour over onions. Roast at 400° for 45 minutes, basting occasionally, until tender.

title: clam chowder perfection(this chowder is finished in the time it takes to boil potatoes.)
directions: Place potatoes, onion and bacon in pan and nearly cover them with water and clam liquid.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: date cookies
directions: Cook dates, water, 1/2 cup sugar and nuts until thick.
Cool. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and blend in 1/2 cup sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in vanilla and flour mixture.
Mix until dough is smooth.
Divide dough into 2 equal parts.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Spread with 1/2 of date mix.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Chill and cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Do the same with other half.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: new england corned beef dinner
directions: Wipe corned beef with damp paper towels.
Place in large kettle; cover with cold water.
Add garlic, cloves, black peppers and bay leaves.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat, and simmer 5 minutes.
Skim surface, then simmer, covered, 3 to 4 hours or until meat is fork-tender.
Add carrots, potatoes and onions during last 25 minutes.
Add cabbage during last 20 minutes.
Cook just until vegetables are tender.

title: meat ball stew
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Shape into 12 balls; brown in fat.
Blend remaining sauce mix with gravy and water.
Add to meat with vegetables; simmer covered 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spinach rockefellar
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a greased baking pan.
Serve with a scooper.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Soften and spread first four ingredients in a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Spread spaghetti sauce on top. Sprinkle with pepperoni, onion and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Fold broccoli into mixture of soup, mayo, cheese and egg.
Top with cracker crumbs.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well until mixture forms a ball. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the last 3 ingredients; pour over first mixture.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove bones and skin.
Place chicken in greased casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cook broccoli as package directs; drain and place on top of chicken.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over broccoli.
Mix both soups in pan with 1/2 cup water and heat.
Pour soup over chicken, broccoli and cheese. Moisten stuffing with chicken broth.
Put stuffing on top and place in a 350° oven until brown and soup is bubbly.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl. Top with 1/3 each of the wafers, bananas and pudding. Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding. Chill thoroughly. Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line 10 muffin tins with paper baking cups.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg substitute, oil and applesauce.
Mix just until moist.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 425° for 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: rachel's pound cake
directions: Blend Crisco, butter and sugar until consistency of whipped cream.
Add flavoring, fresh orange juice and rind.
Add salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing with spatula from bottom to blend with butter and sugar.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Then add 1/2 teaspoon of baking powder.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Put tamales in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with chili. Cover with grated cheese.
Crumble Fritos, put over cheese.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 350°
until bubbles.

title: fruit cocktail nut crisp
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, reserving 1/3 cup of syrup.
Spoon fruit and reserved syrup into shallow baking dish.
Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Spread over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: black bean soup
directions: Rinse beans, discarding any shriveled beans.
Soak in cold water.
Cook 2 hours or until soft.
Remove seeds from peppers and place peppers in boiling water 15 minutes.
Grind together peppers, onions, garlic and cilantro and saute.
Blend cooked beans in blender or food processor in small batches.
Add bouillon cubes and black pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring often.

title: super yogurt
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl.
Eat immediately or refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; then add eggs.
Cream with 1 cup ripe bananas.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder, nuts and salt. Add to cream mixture

title: cheese waffles with sauce
directions: Add the grated cheese to the biscuit mix and blend well.
Add the milk, melted shortening and butter flavoring and stir into the biscuit mix.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy and fold into batter.

title: crab roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up tortillas, starting from one side to the other.
Wrap individually with plastic wrap.
Chill overnight.
Cut into 1-inch slices and serve.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Vitamin A:
For Acceptance.
It stands for new life in Christ. Christ died for our sins, by accepting Him, we get new life. John 1:12.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix jello with cake mix.
Add other ingredients.
Beat 8 minutes on medium speed of mixer.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chinese fish fillets
directions: Heat broiler. For sauce: Mix broth and thickener in a small bowl, stir until thickener dissolves. Heat oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Stir-fry garlic and ginger for 30 seconds. Add rice wine vinegar, soy sauce, sugar substitute and broth mixture. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly,1 minute. Remove from heat.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oleo and quick oats.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Stir all together with the oat mixture.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Milnot and margarine.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chips and Creme.
Stir until smooth, using electric mixer.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine all and pour into buttered dish.
Cover with Topping.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water until barely tender.
Drain and set aside.
Fry bacon and drain on paper towels.
Add onion and celery to fat.
Saute until tender.
Stir in flour and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Heat until bubbly.
Add water, vinegar and sugar.
Stir and boil 1 minute.
Add parsley and bacon.
Heat oven to 350°. Peel and cut potatoes in 1/4-inch pieces.
Combine all in casserole.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes.
Stir in radishes.
Serves 4.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Mix water and milk. Cut chicken and dip in liquid. Put dry ingredients in paper bag. Heat shortening to near smoking.

Take chicken from liquid; put one at a time in paper bag and shake. Put in skillet. Brown both sides, covered tightly. Turn heat low and cook 40 minutes. Uncover; turn heat up to crisp the chicken, 5 to 10 minutes, turning once.

title: bean dip
directions: In a casserole dish, spread beans on bottom.
In a bowl, mix the ground beef, seasoning mix, sour cream, cheese and picante sauce together.
Pour over beans and top with cheese.
Bake in dish at 350° for about 15 minutes or until it bubbles.
Serve with chips.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove bones and skin from salmon.
Save juice from salmon. Mash salmon and add other ingredients.
Stir well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use ring mold, if desired.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add milk, salt, cocoa and vanilla. Stir in 1/2 c. of sugar at a time until dissolved.
Bring to a boil and let boil for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and then oats. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: ma davis' buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer 2 1/2 minutes.
Add flavoring. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Beat 3 1/2 minutes at medium speed.
Do not overbeat or cake will fall.
Place in greased and floured loaf pan, 10 x 5 x 3-inches.
May overflow if pan is too small.
Bake in slow oven preheated at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix using package directions. Pour 1/2 of cake mix in greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Melt caramels with evaporated milk and margarine in microwave. Mix well. Pour over cake. Layer on chocolate chips, pecans and remaining batter. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: fudge cake
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa, water and Crisco to a boil. Mix together the flour and
sugar
and	add to first mixture.
Add soda to the buttermilk and	add
this to the batter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake
at
325° for 25 minutes or less in a sheet pan.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add all other ingredients. Shape dough into small balls. Bake on greased cookie sheet 12 minutes at 400°. Sprinkle with powdered sugar just before serving. These may be frozen.

title: pasta pizza
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Combine eggs and milk and stir into cooked macaroni.
Stir in cheddar cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Spread mixture evenly over a buttered 14 inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Pack sliced cucumbers, onion and dill in jars with celery seed.
Mix vinegar, water, salt and sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour mixture over cucumbers while piping hot.
Seal jars.

title: uncle chieftain's pimiento cheese
directions: Grate cheese, add juice of pimientos, Pet milk, chopped pimientos, relish, mayonnaise, salt and sugar.
Blend well.
I use electric mixer.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla.
Let sit 1 hour.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda and sugars.
Add to egg mixture.
Add shortening.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Add cinnamon.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a glass.
Dip glass in water as needed to prevent dough from sticking.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crisp tortilla chips. Makes 2 cups.

title: sweet and spicy salsa
directions: In medium bowl, combine pineapple, red and yellow pepper, onion, cilantro, jalapeno pepper, lime juice, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes before serving.

title: venison roast
directions: Place venison roast on heavy aluminium foil.
Cover with one envelope onion soup.
Place three or four slices of bacon on top. Seal foil and bake in 300° oven 3 hours or until tender.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: aunt babe's cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate with margarine in pan on low.
Stir in nuts until well coated.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Mix only until well blended.
Don't beat.
Add chocolate mixture and carefully mix.
Fill cupcake cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: moist banana cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients (except sugar) in bowl.
Add oil, buttermilk and bananas.
Beat eggs until foamy and thick. Gradually add sugar.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Caramel or Cream Cheese Icing.

title: super cheesy noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain excess grease.
Boil noodles until done.
Grease deep casserole dish to prevent sticking.
Combine all ingredients except one half of Cheddar cheese.
Season with spices.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 325° or until bubbly.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Bring 1/2 cup chicken broth to a boil in a soup kettle.
Stir in Butter Buds.
Add green onions and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add water chestnuts.
Remove pot from heat and add pepper and herbs.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Add egg whites and chicken broth, using enough to make a dressing which is neither dry nor soggy.

title: baked apples
directions: Core the apples and pare a strip on top of each.
Place in
a 10	x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Fill apples with 3/4 cup raisins.
Combine
granulated
sugar,
brown
sugar, corn syrup, water and oleo.
Bring to a boil and add rum flavoring. Pour
hot syrup
over and around apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 1 hour.
Baste occasionally.

title: rhendy's zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini with seasonings for 10 minutes.
Line 10-inch pie pan with crescent rolls pressed into pan.
Cover dough with mustard.
Beat eggs and add cheese.
Cook at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May be topped with spaghetti sauce.

title: flavored whip
directions: Pour the cream into a bowl; add the drink mix crystals to taste and beat into whipped cream. Yield: About 8 servings.

title: e-z egg custard pie
directions: Melt oleo in 9-inch pie plate.
Mix sugar and flour together until lumps are smoothed out.
Mix eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add to the flour mixture.
Pour over the melted oleo.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: simple cranberry sauce
directions: The cooking time is for fresh berries-if using frozen berries, do not defrost before use; just add 2 minutes to simmering time. Bring water, sugar and salt to a boil in medium saucepan over high heat, stirring occasionally to dissolve sugar.
Then stir in cranberries and return to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium, simmer until slightly thickened and about 2/3 of berries have popped open (about 5 minutes).
Transfer to bowl, cool to room temperature and serve.
(Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before serving.) Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: chicken and peaches
directions: Dip chicken pieces in flour and brown.
Heat together remaining ingredients, except peaches, and pour over chicken about last 1/2 hour of cooking time.
Add peaches and heat thoroughly.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Empty potato slices into a 3-quart round casserole dish.
Stir in sauce mix, tomatoes, water and oregano.
Cover and microwave 10 minutes, stirring twice during cooking.
Stir in pepperoni; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and microwave 7 minutes, stirring after 3 1/2 minutes.
Uncover and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Use fresh, firm medium cucumbers. Wash and cut into quarters. Pour boiling water over them and let stand overnight.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together and chill.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar and set aside. Mix pudding mixes with milk until thick.
Add to cream cheese mixture and stir.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix well.
May thin or stretch with another cup of sour cream. Serve with chips or vegetables.
Serves 20.

title: joyce motson's 6 week muffins
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Stir. Store in refrigerator; do not stir again.
Spoon just enough in muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon whipper snappers
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Mix ingredients by hand, not electric mixer.
Drop by spoonful into powdered sugar and place on cookie sheets.
These are kinda' gooey and a little hard to handle at this point, but well worth the mess.
Bake about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Enjoy.

title: butterscotch bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place bread cubes in buttered 2 1/2-cup casserole.
Beat eggs slightly; stir in margarine, milk, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and raisins.
Pour mixture over bread cubes.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, approximately 40 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or Cool Whip. Yields 2 servings.

title: sassy onion dip
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Stir before serving. Serve with fresh vegetables or chips.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mold wine
directions: Mix sugar and water together, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Do not let it boil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs.
Spread cracker mixture on bottom of shallow casserole.
Save some of mixture to use later.
Mix sour cream, soup and chicken broth.
Add sour cream, soup and broth mixture on top of crackers.
Slice up chicken into small pieces and add to top of other mixture.
Spread rest of crackers on top.
Bake in 325° oven until brown and bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 4 pieces each.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Toss with pieces of biscuits.
Drop in Bundt pan, which has been greased.
Melt the butter, brown sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon. Bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let set 1 minute before turning upside down onto plate.

title: chip beef dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients thoroughly (except pecans, they go on the top).
Use 8-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve hot.
Very good with Triscuits.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream
butter.	Gradually
add	sugar,	creaming
until light and
fluffy.
Beat	for
10 minutes on electric mixer or longer by hand.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add eggs one
at a time to cream mixture, beating well after each addition.	Add flour mixture alternately with milk and flavoring, beating	until smooth.
Bake
batter
in
greased and floured 9-inch
pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.	Top with favorite icing.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Spread cooked chicken breasts on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread cream of celery soup (no water added) on top of chicken.
Mix cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup and the can of Veg-All (drained) together and pour on top of cream of celery soup.
Mix melted margarine and flour together and add milk to form a creamy mixture.
Pour on top and bake for one hour or until brown at 350°.

title: johnny musetti
directions: Brown meat, onions and pepper, stirring occasionally.
Add pimentos, mushrooms and tomatoes; simmer until tender.
Boil noodles and drain.
Mix all together in casserole.
Slice cheese on top.
Bake until brown (approximately 1/2 hour).
Serves 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from first 3 fruits.
Cook with pudding until bubbly. Cool and toss with fruit.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in glass baking dish (greased).
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: to freeze sweet corn
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Boil sweet corn, sugar, salt and water. Stir to keep from sticking.
Heat until it starts to boil and cook 1 minute.
Cool in cold water and freeze.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: *If can't find, use Catalina sweet and sour dressing.

title: chicken wings
directions: Place chicken wings on a broiler pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Combine dry ingredients in a saucepan. Stir in liquids. Cook, stirring constantly until thick, then boil 2 minutes. Remove wings from oven and brush with sauce and return to oven. Bake an additional 40 minutes, basting wings with sauce several times and turning each time you baste.

title: country fried steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Mix the next 3 ingredients.
Dredge steak in flour mixture; lightly pound floured steak.
Cook steak in hot oil in skillet until brown.
Turn steak 1 time.
Add sliced onions and water.
Cover; reduce the heat. Simmer 30 minutes.
Remove the steak; save drippings in skillet. Add 1/4 cup flour to drippings.
Stir until smooth.
Cook until brown.
Gradually add milk and coffee; cook over medium heat. Stir constantly until thick.
Stir in last 3 ingredients.
Serve steak with gravy.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients and serve as a dip with your favorite vegetables.

title: gourmet chicken in foil
directions: If desired, bone and skin chicken breasts.
Brown chicken breasts in margarine.
Place 2 pieces of chicken on double thick 12-inch squares of foil.
Season each with salt, pepper and chives. Divide dry sour cream sauce and mushrooms among the foil packets. Spoon on wine.
Seal packets and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serves 8.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put bread and raisins in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over bread and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dried beef cheese spread
directions: Soften cheese and mix with all ingredients.
Chill.
Small sandwich, celery, crackers, etc.

title: corn meal gravy
directions: Mix corn meal and oil in skillet and brown well.
Add salt and pepper.
Add cream and water; boil until it thickens.

title: fresh veggie salad
directions: Put all veggies in a large bowl (I use Tupperware's largest covered container bowl).
Pour entire bottle of dressing over veggies and marinate overnight.
Do not drain the marinade off but periodically "toss" and respread the dressing.
This makes enough to serve 12 to 15 people.
It's good for potlucks and it "keeps" well in fridge.

title: passion cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare cake per instructions on box, 9 x 13 glass pan. In saucepan, combine pineapple with juice and sugar. Cook over medium heat until sugar is melted. Leave cake in pan. Using a fork, punch holes over all the cake while it is hot. Spread pineapple mixture over hot cake. Chill with cover.

title: whole wheat waffles
directions: Place the flours, baking soda and cinnamon in a medium-sized mixing bowl.
In a smaller bowl, beat the egg and add the buttermilk and oil.
Lightly oil and then heat the waffle iron. Stir the egg mixture into the dry ingredients just until combined. Bake the batter on the hot waffle iron.

title: scripture cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Bake in a 350° oven in a well-greased and floured cake pan until toothpick comes out clean.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat together eggs, cream and 1/2 can of corn.
In a separate bowl, mix remaining corn, creamed corn, sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Mix together with first mixture and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until knife comes out clean.
Serve immediately.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add pineapple and nuts.
On flat side of vanilla wafer, add 1 teaspoon pineapple mixture. Cover with another wafer.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Roll in coconut. Place in cupcake paper.
Refrigerate after all cookies are iced.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Combine soup, soup mix and milk.
Set aside 1/2 cup.
Place rice in buttered casserole.
Pour soup mixture on rice.
Top with chicken and 1/2 cup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: bean burgers
directions: Heat soup in microwave until it's hot.
Mix cooked hot dogs in soup.
Place rolls on paper plates or microwave dish and spoon soup mixture on rolls.
Top each with a slice of cheese and heat until cheese is melted.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: Combine hamburger, rice and soup in casserole dish.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar and flour, then add milk (mix egg yolks with 1/4 cup milk, then add to mixture); mix well. Add 2 cups of water and flavoring, mixing well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until pie thickens.
Remove from heat. Add tablespoon of butter and beat to smooth.
Put into 2 (9-inch) deep pie shells.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Put on top of pie. Put in oven on broil until lightly golden brown.

title: hawaiian pineapple frosty refresher
directions: In a punch bowl, dissolve sugar in lemon juice.
Blend in Hawaiian pineapple juice, cranberry juice and lemon-lime soda. Add sherbet, stirring until softened and partially dissolved. Garnish with kabobs of pineapple chunks.
Makes 48 (4 ounce) servings.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Heat to boiling point the butter, milk, tuna, cheese, salt and pepper.
Drain noodles.
Add sauce.
Put in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and thyme
directions: Coat the chicken in 1 to 2 tablespoons flour.
Brown for 5 minutes in 1 tablespoon oil.
Turn and brown for another 5 minutes in the 2nd tablespoon oil.
Remove chicken from pan.
Add butter and chopped onion with the rest of the flour and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth, lemon juice, thyme and wine.
Stir until thickened and simmering.
Add chicken and cook gently, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Good with rice.

title: six week muffins
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir only until combined.
Fill greased muffin tins half full with batter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yields 50 to 60 muffins.
Batter will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa.
Mix well until no lumps and looks smooth.
Add peanut butter, vanilla extract and dash of salt.
Stir carefully without splashing out of pan.
Add 10x sugar, stirring into other ingredients the milk to proper consistency.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise.
Place one slice of ham on a tortilla.
Spread cream cheese mixture over ham slices.
Sprinkle lightly with chopped green onions.
Roll up tightly and secure with toothpicks.
Cover and chill until serving time.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing, broth, margarine, salt, pepper, sage, onion, celery, put 2/3 of stuffing mixture in casserole dish.
Tear chicken breasts into small pieces, place in dish, mix sour cream and mushroom soup together, pour over chicken then cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: super chili
directions: Grill or fry hamburger patties, then place on towel to drain. Add hot salsa to skillet with kidney beans, cumin, water and tomato paste over medium heat.
Crumble hamburger into mixture.
Reduce heat and simmer.

title: banana shake
directions: Pour ingredients into a blender and push liquify.

title: original new york cheese cake
directions: Put in Cuisinart.
Mix and pour into graham cracker crusts. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Top with cherries (or your own topping) after cooling.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in buttermilk 1 hour.
Add egg and beat well. Add sugar and mix.
Add flour, sifted with salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add cool shortening.
Bake in greased muffin pans in hot oven (400°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine
sugar,
cocoa, cornstarch, salt, egg yolks and milk; cook until thick.
Cool; add butter and vanilla.
Spread over chilled crust and return to refrigerator.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: pizza english muffins(for large crowd)
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate 8 to 16 hours.
Spread evenly on toasted English muffins.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: shish kabob marinade
directions: Add meat and mushrooms. Marinate 24 hours.
Use leftover marinade to baste kabobs while grilling.

title: snicker salad
directions: Cut Snicker bars into bite size pieces.
Cut apples into bite sizes pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine broccoli, 2/3 cup stuffing, corn, egg, 2 tablespoons butter, onion, salt and pepper.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix 1 cup stuffing mix and 1/2 stick oleo together; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ham and corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake at 325° about 45 minutes or until firm.
Yields 2 servings.

title: genoa minestrone soup(serves 20 cups)
directions: In an 8-quart saucepan, saute onions, celery, parsley and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in beef broth, water, wine, tomatoes, tomato sauce, cabbage, carrots, basil and pepper.
Salt to taste (optional).
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, an additional 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables and spaghetti are tender.
Serve and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: footballs
directions: Mix together the margarine, eggs and sugar.
Add the flour and baking powder alternating with the milk and vanilla.
Mixture will be soft.
Heat oil in a frying pan and drop 1 tablespoon of batter in the hot oil until it is finished.
They will puff up and resemble footballs.
After they are cooled, toss them in a paper bag containing confectioners sugar.

title: quick oyster dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dressing, oysters and soup.
Bring to boil in oven.
Slow the heat and simmer about 25 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: roast in a crock-pot
directions: Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 8 to 10 hours.

title: no fool pie
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour flour mixture into butter in pan.
Place peaches around in batter. Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
When done, pour juice of fruit over crust.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order listed.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Add meal mix, oil and sugar.
Pour into greased small iron skillet that has meal sprinkled over bottom of it.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lazy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in oblong pan.
Mix flour, milk, and sugar in bowl.
Pour margarine in this flour mixture.
Pour peaches in pan and pour flour mixture over the peaches.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: north carolina pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold in sugar, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix nuts and cracker crumbs.
Then add to egg mixture. Line 10-inch buttered pie pan.
Bake at 325°.
Remove from oven and after crust has cooled and flallen into place, fill center with cream.
Top with frozen fruit and top with whipped cream.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel, core and halve apples.
Set aside.
In a medium bowl, mix together flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Pour in milk. Stir until mixture resembles pie crust dough.
With a spoon, remove 1/2 cup dough.
Roll out on a floured surface until 1/8-inch thick.
Carefully wrap around 1 apple half, folding dough in an overlapping fashion.
Place seam side down, in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Repeat with remaining dough and apple halves.

title: baked corn bread
directions: Mix sour cream, corn, eggs and oil together.
Add Jiffy mix. Spray pan and bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: shadow pie
directions: Beat egg yolks in top of double boiler and gradually add milk. Blend cornstarch and 1/2 cup sugar and add.
Cook over hot water stirring constantly until mixture coats a metal spoon.
Dissolve 1 cup chocolate bits in 1 1/2 cups of the mixture.
Add vanilla. Pour in pastry shell.
Soften gelatin in water 5 minutes. Dissolve in remaining egg mixture and cool.
Beat egg whites until frothy and gradually beat in remaining sugar.
Fold into gelatin mixture and pour over chocolate layer.
Chill.
Chip remaining chocolate bits and sprinkle over top of pie.
Approximate yield, 8 portions.

title: orzo soup
directions: In a small amount of oil, fry onion and pepper.
Add hamburger and cook until brown.
Drain grease.
Add Veg-All, tomatoes, water, bouillon and soup mix.
Cook until mixed well.
Add macaroni and cook until tender.

title: mustard butter
directions: Blend the mustard, sugar and flour thoroughly.
Add salt. Blend dry mixture into beaten egg and milk.
Cook carefully over direct heat, if desired.
(Some use a double boiler.) As it begins to thicken, add 1/2 cup vinegar and butter/oleo, cooking to desired consistency.
Cool.
Good with ham, corned beef, etc.

title: corn dogs(makes 12)
directions: Mix together ingredients and put dried hot dogs into batter, 1 at a time.
Fry until golden brown.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each.
Sift cake flour and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla before last flour.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: apricot marmalade
directions: Cook and boil first 4 ingredients for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Take off fire.
Add jello.
Put in jar.
Seal.

title: fry-baked dolphin
directions: Cut thinly sliced dolphin into serving size pieces.
Mix together eggs and milk.
Dip fish in egg and milk mixture and let soak.
Bread with Ritz crackers (crushed).
Put fish on foil-covered cookie sheet.
Spread a dollop of mayo on each piece of fish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken and yellow rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from bone and cut into bite size pieces. Cook yellow rice in 4 cups of broth until done.
Saute bell pepper, onion and celery with pork sausage until all are done. Toss together sausage mixture and rice.
Layer rice mixture and chicken in casserole dish.
Spread mushroom soup on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chiles rellenos(mexican stuffed peppers)
directions: Broil peppers 2-inches from heat, turning until blistered. Place peppers in a bag and close until cool enough to handle. Peel peppers and remove stems and seeds.
Stuff each pepper with 1/2 cup cheese.
Set aside.

title: turkey breast(the low-fat way)
directions: Skin turkey breast.
Place in roaster.
Add pears.
Pour apple juice over all.
Cover.
Bake at 325° until done.
The broth makes delicious gravy.

title: my boss's yummy casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion. Add rice, seasonings, tomatoes, catsup and water. Simmer about 40 to 45 minutes or until rice is done.

title: french cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Melt butter.
Add sugar and beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for ten to twelve minutes.

title: broiled chicken wings
directions: Cut wings in two pieces, discarding tips.
Place on shallow dish.
Combine lemon juice, soy sauce and onion powder.
Pour over chicken and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight. Drain wings, reserving 1 tablespoon marinade.
Place wings on foil-lined broiler pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine reserved marinade with honey and catsup, stirring well.
Brush half mixture on wings.
Broil (in preheated broiler) 6 to 7 inches for about 7 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining sauce.
Broil an additional 7 minutes.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.
Increase recipe proportionately.

title: jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: Put peppers through food grinder (fine).
Use all juice from ground peppers.
Slowly boil all ingredients for 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add liquid pectin and boil for 1 minute.
Pour into 1/2 pint jars.
Seal.
Process in water bath for 5 minutes. Yields five (8 ounce) jars.
Use gloves to grind peppers.

title: coconut walnut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine sugar and oil. Add eggs and vanilla and beat on medium speed until well blended. Alternately add buttermilk and flour, beating well after each addition.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Spoon batter into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour or until top springs back when touched.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir constantly.
Boil to hard ball stage (260°).
Add butter and pour over popcorn.
Form into balls.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and water in saucepan.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally to 236° or until a few drops form a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Cool at room temperature without stirring until lukewarm, or until the hand can be held comfortably on the bottom of pan.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and butter.
Beat until thick and pour into buttered plate or square dish.

title: valentine's day salad
directions: Dissolve candies in boiling water in saucepan on stove. Add jello and stir until dissolved. Add applesauce. Place in 9 x 9-inch pan or small rectangular dish to congeal. Cut into squares or cut into heart shapes. Serve with dollop of mayonnaise.

title: do-it-all marinade
directions: Place onion in a large Ziploc bag. Pour in soy sauce and lemon juice. Add black pepper; close bag and shake. Add meat of your choice. Let marinate for at least 30 minutes but no longer than 1 hour. Grill to desired doneness. Discard leftover marinade. If using as a sauce, place all ingredients in a bowl, stir and cover. Let sit for at least one hour at room temperature or can be refrigerated for up to a day.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together. Place in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian cheesecake
directions: Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Use an electric mixer, a food processor or a blender to beat Ricotta cheese until smooth.
Gradually add sugar and egg yolks, beating each addition.
Beat in flour, grated lemon rind and vanilla.

title: broccoli, cauliflower, pea salad
directions: Mix dressing mix with sour cream and mayonnaise until smooth. Mix dressing with vegetables to coat vegetables.
Serve on a salad plate on a lettuce leaf dark green in color for contrast.

title: scones
directions: Mix to sponge; let rise for 1 hour.
Mix enough flour to make soft firm dough.
Knead, cover and let rise 1 hour.
Pour out on board; roll flat.
Cut and let rise until light.
Fry in oil at 375°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Some go to church to take a walk;

title: ice cream jello
directions: Mix strawberry jello to boiling water, then beat ice cream with junior mixer.
Cream with junior mixer, then pour into mold and let set 1/2 hour in fridge.

title: dirt
directions: Combine butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Add milk and pudding. Beat at low speed until smooth. Mix in Cool Whip. Alternate layers of Oreo cookies and cream cheese mixture with Oreo layer on top. Freeze 3 hours. Thaw in fridge approximately 1 hour before serving.

title: jane's cake
directions: Sift together and add buttermilk, shortening, egg and vanilla. Beat well.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
(Carob powder may be substituted for cocoa if a different flavor is desired.)

title: quick pizza snacks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Remove dough from can.
Do not unroll.
Cut roll into 12 slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 1-inch apart, cut side down.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven. Spoon about 1 teaspoon sauce on each slice; sprinkle cheese over sauce.
Bake for 3 to 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Serve warm.
Makes 12 snacks.

title: squash casserole
directions: Bake at 400° until done.

title: angel cornbread
directions: Warm milk enough to melt yeast and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pastel pound cake
directions: Dump and mix.
Spray pan with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° until done.
Let cool and frost with following icing.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape.

title: egg nog
directions: Pour egg nog into punch bowl.
Pour in rum and stir.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill in refrigerator.
Stir.
Top with nutmeg.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Bring the milk and Crisco to barely a boil. Add the sugar and salt. Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Add to milk mixture which you have let cool. Add 4 cups flour. Cover and let rise about 15 to 30 minutes. Stir down and add about 4 more cups flour. Put into refrigerator until ready to use.
It keeps for about a week or you can partially bake and then freeze.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry yeast and warm water and set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, and soda together.
Combine yeast and melted shortening to warm buttermilk and add sifted ingredients and sugar.
Pour this out onto floured board and knead until desired consistency.
Roll out and cut with glass or biscuit cutters. Bake at 400 degrees until golden brown.
Makes about 36 biscuits depending on size.
I butter the top of mine before I bake them.

title: fruit cocktail cake with topping
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until dissolved.
Add syrup, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add oats and coconut; mix.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: bread pudding mom made
directions: Beat egg in a 1-quart baking dish; add remaining ingredients. Mix well and bake until light brown at 350°.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Mix eggs, sugar, salt and vinegar in blender.
Stir flour into bacon.
Add blender mixture and water to bacon.
Heat over medium-high heat until thickened.
Pour over dandelions, endive, lettuce, etc.
Serves 4.

title: fun for kids
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold cream.
Add water and stir.
Add good coloring to obtain color you want and paint on with a paintbrush.

title: swiss salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, cream, mustard, salt and pepper. Refrigerate.
Mix salad greens, cheese and olives in a large bowl. Just before serving, toss mixture with chilled dressing and Bac*Os.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue turkey
directions: Mix water and salt together, then add remaining ingredients. Inject into turkey the night before preparation.
(Inject with a large needle syringe a little in a spot; don't stick the whole syringe full in one spot.)
Set in the refrigerator overnight. Bake as you usually do or put in pan on grill and baste frequently.

title: eggs and sausage or bacon
directions: Brown sausage or bacon; drain.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard.
Add cubed bread and stir.
Add cheese and meat.
Pour into baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can refrigerate overnight before baking.

title: lemon brownies
directions: Mix and pour on top of cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mini meat loaves and vegetables
directions: Combine ground beef, salt, eggs, 1/2 cup catsup, bread crumbs and chopped onion.
Shape into 3 mini-loaves.
Put in a 10-inch square baking dish.
Place sliced vegetables around and between loaves.
Salt and pepper; pour remaining catsup over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Stir vegetables, cover and cook an additional 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook another 15 minutes.
Let stand awhile for better slicing.

title: banana-honey-bran bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in cereal and nuts.
Beat egg slightly in a small bowl, then beat in honey, oil, milk and bananas.
Add banana mixture all at once to dry ingredients and stir just until flour is dampened. Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Wrap in foil or plastic.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mash vanilla wafers.
Add sugar and baking powder.
Beat eggs, milk and butter.
Add coconut, nuts and pineapple.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350°.

title: skillet potatoes
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook vegetables and garlic until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add broth, water, potatoes, carrots and seasoning to skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Uncover; over medium heat, simmer 5 minutes or until broth is slightly thickened, stirring often.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 6.
Contains approximately 140 to 150 calories per serving.

title: french frying batter
directions: Combine egg, oil and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Add ice water and flour.
Mix until smooth.
Batter may be used for shrimp, chicken, onion rings, squash, okra, etc.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is still hot, punch holes in cake with meat fork. Pour milk and cream of coconut over cake. Freeze overnight. Ice with Cool Whip. Sprinkle coconut over cake. Keep refrigerated.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in oil, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Beat in zucchini, sifted flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and baking powders.
Then fold in nuts.
Bake in two well-greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Peel and cut peaches into 1/2-inch thick slices.
In large bowl, toss sliced peaches with flour, lemon juice, salt, 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Spoon mixture into 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil; bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Mixture should be hot and bubbly.
About 15 minutes before peaches are cooked, separate biscuits.
Cut each one into quarters.
In medium size bowl, mix 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add biscuit pieces and toss to coat.
Remove baking dish from oven; remove foil.
Top peach mixture with biscuit mixture in single layer; sprinkle any sugar left in bowl over biscuits.
Return to oven, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Cool on wire rack 10 to 20 minutes to serve warm.
Serves 12.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Whisk together the milk, buttermilk, egg, salad oil, sugar, salt and baking powder.

Add the cornmeal and flour and mix well. Fold in diced red pepper, chopped jalapenos and whole kernel corn. Place in an 8-inch round greased pan or a greased cast-iron skillet and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: date cake
directions: Take dates, boiling water and soda and put in mixing bowl. Stir, then let stand until cool.
Cream butter, sugar and egg into date mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in flour, then add nuts. Bake 13 x 9-inch baking dish at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: green chili cheese squares
directions: Put 1/2 of cheese on bottom of greased 9x13 pan. Place green chilies over cheese. Pour egg mixture over chilies and cheese. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350 for 35-45 minutes. Cool and cut in bite size squares.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and place in baking dish. Top with nuts and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: pork roast
directions: Season shoulder with mixer of next seven ingredients.
Cut onion up into roaster.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: dilly cheese batter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda and egg; add yeast mixture and beat until it forms a stiff dough.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk, 50 to 60 minutes.
Pat down and turn into a well-greased tube pan.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and brush with garlic butter.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix yeast with 2 tablespoons warm water. Combine remaining ingredients and yeast mixture. Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake in hot 400° oven for 20 minutes or until done and as brown as desired.

title: corn chowder soup
directions: Fry bacon (2 or 3 strips) until crisp.
Remove bacon and fry onion until limp.
Add potatoes and water; boil until potatoes are done.
Add corn, milk, salt and ham.
Top with cheese and bacon. Simmer.

title: caraway rye bread(for bread machine)
directions: Measure ingredients into baking pan.
Insert baking pan securely into baking unit; close lid.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients in a saucepan until thickened.
Use as a baste.
May be used freely!

title: ginger pears
directions: Peel and quarter pears; remove cores.
Combine apple juice, red wine and ginger in medium saucepan.
Place pears in poaching liquid.
Bring to boil; reduce to simmer and cover.
Cook about 15 minutes or until pears are tender.
Remove pears and set aside. Continue to cook, poaching liquid until thickened slightly to form a thin sauce (about 10 minutes).
Return pears to sauce, turning to coat thoroughly.
Place in serving dishes, spooning the sauce over the pears.

title: egg nog
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Keeps several days.

title: party punch
directions: Combine drink mix, gelatin and sugar in a large bowl.
Add 1 cup boiling water; stir until sugar dissolves.
Stir in pineapple juice and 2 quarts cold water.
Can be frozen.
Add ginger ale; stir until slushy.
Yields 1 1/2 gallons.

title: cheese and onion enchiladas
directions: In a saucepan, combine soup, chillies and sour cream.
Heat and reserve for sauce.
Saute corn tortillas in oil for 2 to 3 seconds on each side.
Drain.
Shred the cheese and chop the onions fine. Put 1 to 2 tablespoons cheese and onions into each tortilla.
Roll and place seam side down in a large greased casserole dish.
Pour sauce over top of tortillas.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cheese over the top and return to oven until cheese bubbles.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Scrub potatoes. Pierce potatoes to allow steam to escape. Bake about 45 minutes or until tender. Let stand until cool enough to handle. Cut potatoes lengthwise into fourths; carefully scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shells. Save potato pulp for another use. Set oven control to broil. Place potato shells, skin side down, on rack in broiler pan. Brush with butter. Broil with tops 4 to 5-inches from heat 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp and brown. Sprinkle tomato and cheese and broil until cheese is melted. Top with fat-free sour cream. Sprinkle with green onions.

title: italian bread
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Add margarine.
