Gradually add tap water to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 3/4 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes. Cover with plastic wrap, then a towel.
Let rest 20 minutes. Divide dough in half.
Roll each half into an oblong 15 x 10-inch.
Beginning at wide side, roll up tightly.
Pinch seam to seal.
Taper ends by rolling gently back and forth.
Place on greased baking sheet sprinkled with corn meal. Brush dough with oil. Cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
When ready to bake, remove from refrigerator, uncover and let stand at room temperature 10 minutes. Make 3 or 4 diagonal cuts on top of each loaf.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven. Brush with 1 egg white mixed with 1 tablespoon water. Return to oven. Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer, until golden brown.

title: egg lemon soup
directions: In large saucepan, heat the broth and season to taste with salt and pepper.
About 10 minutes before serving, beat together eggs and lemon juice until the eggs are light in color.
Remove 1/2 cup hot broth and stir into egg-lemon mixture, a little at a time.
Still stirring, add egg-lemon mixture to remaining broth, cautiously heat until eggs and lemon are evenly combined with broth.
Add cooked rice and serve immediately with garnish of lemon slices.
Serves 6.

title: dog biscuits(your dog will love you)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together until it resembles cornmeal, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Roll 1/2-inch thick. Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Stir together sugar, tapioca and nutmeg.
Add sugar mixture to rhubarb-strawberry pieces; toss to coat fruit.
Let fruit mixture stand for 15 minutes.
Fill a pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate with fruit mixture; dot with butter.
Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Cover edges of pie with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 25 more minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: aunt jean's chocolate syrup
directions: Melt butter and cocoa on low heat.
Take off stove and add sugar and salt.
Slowly add evaporated milk.
Cook until dissolved.

title: cheese grits
directions: Boil grits, salt and cheese; let cool. Add eggs, Worcestershire, garlic, margarine and Tabasco.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix together in bowl: butter, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
In a separate bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Combine both together until smooth.
Crush half of Oreos and put in pan.
Cover with mixture.
Then put other half of crushed Oreos on top.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: creamy yogurt pops
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into popsicle molds.
Freeze for several hours, then enjoy!
(A healthful alternative to ice cream on a warm day.)

title: greek salad
directions: Wash and run a fork down the sides of the cucumbers to make a design so the white shows through the green.
Then slice in thin slices.
Slice the red onion and make thin rings.
Place in bowl and toss; add the rest of the ingredients in a jar and blend, then toss with the cukes and onions.
Chill about 1 hour and serve.

title: green chili and cheese casserole
directions: Mix cheeses together; then layer in an 8 x 8-inch pan in this order:
2 cups of the cheeses, chilies, salt, pepper and then remaining 2 cups of cheese.

title: kitty's cheese ball
directions: Drain fruit well discarding juice.
Mix first 4 ingredients and form into 2 large balls.
Roll in nuts.
Freezes well.

title: stromboli
directions: Separate egg yolks from egg whites.
Grease cookie sheets. Mix the egg yolks and
next 6 ingredients.
Spread over dough. Put on the meat and cheese.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Brush the roll with the egg whites.
Slit top of roll for air.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with mixer.
Bake crescent dinner rolls on cookie sheets at 375° for 10 minutes; cool, then spread the cream cheese mixture on top.
Add chopped broccoli, carrots and cauliflower and cheese on top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Add pumpkin, slightly beaten eggs, oil, then water.
Mix until smooth.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Grease pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaf pans.

title: barbecued kielbasa
directions: Mix all ingredients, except kielbasa.
Place sliced kielbasa in crock-pot and cover with sauce.
Cook on low temperature for 6 or more hours.

title: millionaire pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, fold Cool Whip and milk.
Add thawed lemonade and whip.
Add next 3 ingredients immediately (will start to firm up).
Pour into shells and refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add ice cream and mix well. Then add crushed pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.

title: hamburger-noodle casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger
with	chopped
onion	and drain well. Cook noodles
according to package directions and drain well. (You may not
want
to
use	a whole package of noodles.) Mix together the soup, sauce, sour cream, cream cheese and 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese.
Stir in hamburger and noodles.
Pour into a 9 x
13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and hot.
Last 5 minutes, add other 1/2 of cheese to top and cook just until it melts.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix well the first 10 ingredients.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Brown in fat or oil.
Remove meat, then stir into oil the flour, paprika, salt and pepper, then stir in boiling water and sour cream.
Return meatballs to gravy.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bologna surprise
directions: Generously spread mayonnaise on one slice of bread.
Next, cook bologna in a skillet for 5 minutes, turning frequently.
Add tomatoes to the bread.
Sprinkle salt and pepper onto tomatoes (add as much as your taste buds require.)
Remove grease from bologna by wrapping in a Bounty paper towel.
Add bologna and cheese to bread while still hot so as to melt the cheese.
Layer potato chips until the sandwiches are completely covered.
Press both pieces of bread together firmly.
Serve on a paper plate.

title: cheese soup
directions: Dissolve
bouillon cubes in hot water.
Combine vegetables, parsley
and
seasonings
with bouillon water.
Mix and simmer
30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Mash vegetables.
Add
milk gradually while stirring;
then add flour in the same manner. Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on.
Let cool, peel and grate potatoes.
Put in casserole dish.
In saucepan, melt butter, sour cream and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Mix in chopped onions.
Mix with potatoes.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crunchy cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in ham, onion, mustard, pepper sauce and parsley.
Cover and chill for a few hours.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts to coat. Serve with crackers.

title: hot bittersweet sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate on High in 4-cup measuring cup in microwave.
Stir in other ingredients and cook on High 1 to 2 minutes until sugar melts and mixture comes to a boil.
Remove and add vanilla.
Reheat in microwave before using.

title: red devil balls
directions: Cut cheese into 1-inch pieces and put into blender.
Add deviled ham and blend until smooth.
Remove from container and chill in refrigerator until firm enough to handle.
Shape into small balls; roll in chopped nuts and serve on toothpicks.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: pistachio mousse
directions: Mix crushed pineapple and pudding mix together.
Mix in rest of ingredients and refrigerate.
If desired, can top with chopped nuts.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix well.
This is a good dip for cauliflower, carrot sticks, celery and green peppers.

title: traditional ham loaf
directions: Mix ham, pork, onions, bread crumbs, milk, eggs, prepared mustard (1 teaspoon), parsley and pepper thoroughly.
Press evenly into a loaf pan.
In a cup, mix brown sugar, 1 tablespoon pineapple juice and 1 teaspoon prepared mustard.
Spread over loaf and pour remaining 3 tablespoons pineapple juice over the top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onions and garlic; reduce heat to low and cook about 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add Worcestershire sauce, pepper and oregano.
Simmer 10 additional minutes, stirring frequently.

title: microwave coconut pie
directions: Mix together and cook in microwave 11 minutes on High.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In an oblong pan, spread pecans on the bottom.
On top of that, add a layer of coconut.
Mix cake mix as directed on box. Pour on top of coconut.
Mix butter and cream cheese together, then add confectioners sugar.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil tea bags and make 1/2 gallon weak tea.
Add sugar, lemon juice, pineapple juice and orange juice plus 3 juice cans of water. Put in pot; place cinnamon and allspice in rag and put in pot. Bring to a boil.
Leave spice bag in tea 4 to 5 hours, then remove.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat and add taco seasoning. Add soup, enchilada sauce and chilies.
Bring to a boil, stirring all the ingredients together, then simmer.
Grate cheese.
Layer in a large baking dish the tortillas, meat sauce and cheese 3 times. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake white or yellow cake mix (use whole egg).
Add coconut to mixture.
Bake according to cake directions.
Mix together Eagle Brand and can of cream of coconut.
When cake comes out of oven, gouge it and pour Eagle Brand mixture over it while cake is hot. Let cool.
Layer with Cool Wip and sprinkle coconut over top. Yummy good and moist!

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat egg until light-colored; add sugar.
Mix well.
Stir in melted margarine, flour and milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 1 hour.

title: split pea soup
directions: Place peas in large kettle.
Cover with water; wash well. Drain and cover with 4 quarts of water.
Bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Shut off and let sit overnight or at least 2 hours. When ready, bring to a boil with ham bone or meat.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Remove ham bone; allow to cool. Remove meat and chop.
Add back to soup; cook until thick and smooth.
Season to taste.
Serve with cornbread.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar and cocoa. Mix well, then add remaining ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13 Pyrex dish that has been sprayed with Pam in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Mix scalded milk, sugar and salt.
When lukewarm, add yeast cake softened in about 2 tablespoons lukewarm water.
Add beaten egg white and enough flour to knead, beating in the flour thoroughly while adding.
Knead thoroughly.

When it is smooth and satiny to the touch, keeps its round shape and does not stick to the board or hand, it is ready to be placed in a clean, oiled bowl. Knead in all the flour to be used at this time.
On the other hand, use no more than necessary.
Cover tightly and let rise.
When double in bulk, knead again with just enough flour to keep from sticking.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with a medium size biscuit cutter, spread with a thin layer of butter.
Crease through the center with a knife.
Fold over and press the edges close together. Place in a pan far enough apart to prevent them touching even after they are risen.
Let rise again and bake in a hot oven.

title: oven brisket
directions: Place brisket on heavy foil.
Add tenderizer and seasonings. Pour vinegar and barbecue sauce over this and cover tightly in several layers of foil.
Marinate overnight or at least 12 hours. Bake in foil at 325° for 45 minutes per pound.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine mayonnaise, salt, pepper, cayenne, lemon juice, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and chili sauce in a small bowl. Blend well.
Chill.

title: oriental marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate. Good for chicken drummies.

title: munchie mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Keep sealed in airtight container.
Great mix for parties or just to have on hand for easy snacking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Set aside.
In bowls, mix sour cream, soup, stuffing and broccoli.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Place in saucepan with 1/4 cup butter. Heat over medium heat until melted and smooth, stirring often. Place vegetables in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over; mix well.
Melt remaining butter.
Stir in cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mary jo's famous biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
With a pastry blender or two knives, cut in margarine until the mixture is the consistency of cornmeal and peas.
Add the milk and bring the dough together by stirring gently with a flat-edged spoon.
If the mixture is too wet, add more flour.
If it won't come together, add more milk.
Place the dough on a well-floured surface and knead only 13 to 15 times. Roll out the dough to 1-inch thickness (1 thumb knuckle).
Using a biscuit cutter, cut out biscuits.
Bake 15 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen biscuits.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Bake cake mix; cool in refrigerator.
Shake together flour and milk.
Put in saucepan and stir constantly until a paste.
Cool. Set aside.
Mix Crisco, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Cream together then pour in paste mixture.
Whip until creamy.
Cut cake in half and spread on cream.
Put other half of cake on top.
Cut and serve.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: May be flavored with fruit, etc.

title: robin's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana cream supreme
directions: Combine graham crackers, butter and sugar. Press into bottom and up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan. Combine whipped topping, pudding and sour cream in batter bowl. Mix well. Pour half of filling over crust. Slice bananas on top. Pour remaining filling over bananas. Sprinkle pecans over top. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream butter; add powdered sugar and 2 cups flour.
Press mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Mix together the refried beans, green chilies and taco seasoning.
Spread on serving plate or in a dish.
Blend avocados, lemon juice and 1/2 the salsa until smooth.
Spread avocado mixture on top of beans.
Spread sour cream on top of avocado mixture.
Spread the following in order given:
lettuce, cheese, remaining salsa, olives.
Serve with tortilla or corn chips. Serves 8.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Make paste of cocoa and coloring, then add to mixture.
Add salt and flour (that has been sifted 3 times) and vanilla alternately with buttermilk.
Mix completely and beat well, but do not beat soda and vinegar. Sprinkle soda over batter, then pour vinegar over it.
Fold it thoroughly through the batter.
Bake in layers at 350°.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Open spaghetti jar and stir in the oregano, basil and garlic. Pour about 1/3 of sauce evenly into a 7 x 11-inch baking dish, then stir water into remaining sauce and set aside.
Arrange 1/3 of noodles in a single layer in dish.
If used, evenly crumble the uncooked beef on top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of Cheddar cheese, then evenly pour over about 1/3 of the remaining sauce.
Arrange 1/2 of the remaining noodles on top and sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Distribute Ricotta cheese over all, then pour over 1/2 of the remaining sauce.
Add remaining noodles; cover with rest of sauce.
Cover dish with plastic wrap tightly with 2 to 3 wraps. Cook in microwave oven at half power for 10 minutes, turn dish and cook another 10 minutes at half power.
Then let stand in oven, covered, 5 minutes.
Turn dish again and cook, covered, at full power for 14 minutes, turning dish several times.
Uncover lasagna and sprinkle generously Mozzarella, then with Parmesan and cook, covered, for 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Remember, to cook cheese in microwave makes it tough, so less time is better. Remove from oven and let stand covered for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs.
Beat in vanilla, pecans and flour.
Roll into logs.
Chill dough or may be frozen. When ready to use, slice into 1/4 inch cookies.
Place on baking sheet.
Cook approximately 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Mix together and chill.
Roll into balls and place 3 balls in each greased muffin tin.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: jello supreme
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to directions.

Put one-half of Jell-O in a separate bowl and place in freezer until firm. Add to firm Jell-O 2 apples that have been cut into chunks. Mix well. Pour this mixture into an 8 x 10 glass dish. Set in refrigerator.

title: healthful date bread
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine dates and raisins.
Pour boiling water over the fruit.
Set aside; let cool.
In large mixing bowl, add dry ingredients.
Stir egg whites and vanilla in cooled fruit mixture, then add this to flour mixture.
Stir until blended (will be thick).
Spread into lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes (glass dish bake 30 minutes at 325°), or until toothpick comes out dry.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn onto rack.
Wrap and store overnight until ready to serve.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs and sugar for 1 minute until creamy and thick.
Add milk, butter, vanilla, nutmeg and salt and beat well.

title: company chicken
directions: Line bottom of casserole with dried beef.
Wrap each chicken filet with 1 or 2 pieces of bacon.
Place on top of dried beef.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Mix the ingredients thoroughly in a large bowl.
Pour small amounts of the batter onto a hot, lightly greased griddle or frying pan over medium-high heat.
When bubbles form on the pancakes and the edges begin to brown, flip the pancakes.
Cook a minute or more until brown.
Serve with butter, syrup or honey.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler over simmering water.
Do not boil water in bottom of boiler.
Beat at high speed on electric mixer for 7 minutes.
Frosting will be nice and fluffy.

title: savory pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine all ingredients except pecans and salt.
Spread pecans on a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Pour the butter mixture over the nuts and stir to coat.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle with salt while warm.
Cool and store airtight.

title: beef and eggplant supper
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet, stirring often to crumble beef.
Drain; remove meat and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in oil and butter in a large skillet until tender.
Add eggplant and cook 5 to 7 minutes over medium heat, stirring often. Stir in ground beef and next 6 ingredients.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese and cook just until cheese melts. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening with a fork until it looks like coarse meal.
Add milk slowly.
Toss on floured board.
Knead gently; roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut biscuits. Bake at 400° in a preheated oven for 20 minutes.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Cut whole package of rolls lengthwise.
Put bottom on cookie sheet and spread with half of mixture.
Put layer of ham and layer of cheese on rolls.
Shred rest of mixture on this.
Place top of rolls on this and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: chile verde (green chile sauce)
directions: Heat shortening or oil in medium-size skillet over medium heat.
Saute chopped onion in shortening.
Add flour.
Cook 1 minute.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes. Serve over enchiladas or burritos.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: This is a three layer cake.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon, mixing well.
Combine the beaten eggs and the oil, stirring to mix, and pour into the flour mixture, stirring until the dry ingredients are thoroughly moistened.
Then add and stir in the vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup nuts and the bananas.
Then add another cup of nuts and stir in.
Spoon the batter into three greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes in pans.
Turn out on pastry cloth.
When ready to stack, frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well.
Add 2 cups flour alternately with lemon extract.
Fold in chopped fruit and nuts, dredged with the last 2 cups flour.
Fold in egg whites.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: carrots casserole
directions: Mix carrots, soup and cheese in casserole.
Put bread crumbs and oleo on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper in margarine until crisp (not soft).
Add to bread crumbs; add black pepper and garlic powder.
Then salt to taste.
Stir and mix well.
Add chicken stock next.
Mix well.
Fold (raw) green onions into mixture. Mixture must be real soft.
Add more stock if necessary.
Bake at 350° until dressing is firm and brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 medium loaves.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: baked custard
directions: Heat milk until hot, but not boiling.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add sugar and salt.
Add milk slowly, stirring all the time. Mix in vanilla.
Pour into baking pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon if used.
Bake at 300° (slow oven) for about 1 hour until knife stuck in the center comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings of 2/3 cup each.

title: tomato fish swirls
directions: In medium skillet, heat oil on medium-high.
Saute tomatoes and seasonings 2 minutes until saucy.
Stir in bread crumbs. Cook, stirring, 1 minute longer.
Spread filling evenly on fillets.
Roll up fillets; secure with toothpicks.
Place upright in greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Sprinkle with thyme if desired.
Total Time:
30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: apple-raisin crisp
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°. In a large bowl, toss the apples with the lemon juice, raisins, 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Spoon the mixture into an ungreased 9-inch pan and set aside.

title: sausage bread wreath
directions: This is good the next day, reheated for brunch and served with scrambled eggs, fruit, etc.

title: fanny farmer bars
directions: Cream shortening, cocoa, sugar and eggs together for 2 minutes.
Add dry ingredients; stir in nuts.
Pour into 10 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle miniature marshmallows on top.
Return to oven for 1 1/2 minutes.
Cool completely and frost.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

In a bowl, mix dry (first five) ingredients. In a separate large bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well. Stir dry ingredients into sweet potato mixture. Add pecans, if desired. Knead dough and roll out on a floured surface. Cut dough with a biscuit cutter. Place biscuits on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown. Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen biscuits.

title: artichoke angel hair
directions: Put oil in pan.
Warm.
Put in garlic.
When you smell the garlic, put in artichokes, tomatoes and nuts.
Swirl and cook until warm.
Add pasta and toss.
Add herbs and salt and pepper to taste.
Add Parmesan, either tossed in pasta, or grated on top.

title: chow chow
directions: Cut up all ingredients very fine.
Place in container to cook. Add 2 to 3 tablespoons salt and sugar.
Then add 1 teaspoon pickling spice.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Put mixture on high heat. The secret is not to cook the ingredients too much.
Put in jars and seal while hot.

title: chicken
directions: First you have to kill the chicken.
Then you have to take the feathers off the chicken.
Now, you put the chicken in the oven for hours.
Cook at 25 degrees.
After the chicken is done, put salt and pepper on it and eat.

title: i'll never cook veggies again
directions: Wash and rinse veggies.
Place veggies in a big bowl.
Add cheese and mix well; set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix the sauce with the veggies before ready to serve so veggies stay crisp!

title: leg of lamb
directions: Rub garlic, salt, pepper, oregano and Worcestershire sauce on lamb.
Bake roast at 350°, adding can of consomme and cup of Burgundy wine.
Baste meat frequently and reduce temperature to 325° in last hour of roasting.
If desired, you may add onions, carrots and potato to meat at this time.
For 4 to 6 lb. leg of lamb, cook 2 1/3 to 3 hours for medium done or 3 1/2 to 4 hours for well done.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Turn oven to Toast or to 250°.
Spread the butter on the bread.
Lightly sprinkle cinnamon and sugar onto bread.
Put in oven. Check on it every 2 minutes or until done.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions until just tender.
Pat in a greased casserole.
Next, mix onions, celery, cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread over vegetables.
Melt margarine; mix with crackers and sprinkle over top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Stir.
Add to sugar and butter.
Add eggs and jams.
Stir well.
Sift flour with spices and nuts.
Mix well.
Add whiskey.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: cabbage roll soup
directions: In a medium-size pot, cut up head of cabbage and boil until it is softened.
In a large pot, brown ground beef, eggs and onion together.
Then add sauerkraut, tomato soup, crushed tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until onion is softened.
Add drained, already-cooked cabbage.
Then simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream to taste.

title: chocolate sauce(for white cake)
directions: In small saucepan, combine cocoa, cornstarch, sugar and salt. Stir in hot water and cook over medium heat, stirring all the time, until clear, thick and smooth.
Add butter and vanilla. Serve warm over white cake.
Cut into squares.

title: french toast
directions: In a medium, shallow bowl, mix eggs, milk and pancake mix. Blend well with a fork.
Heat skillet with 2 teaspoons of oleo until hot.
Dip 1 bread slice into the batter and cook in hot skillet 2 minutes on each side, until lightly browned on both sides.
Add more oleo to skillet.
Repeat until you have cooked all bread.

title: tangy cheese spread
directions: Melt Velveeta.	Cube one lb. at a time and microwave on 7 for about 2 minutes.

Then transfer to oven to stay warm and cube and microwave the other pound.	Meanwhile, fry and crumb the bacon. Mix cheese and bacon with the mayonnaise, horseradish and cayenne. Pour into crocks or plastic storage containers.
Will last up to 2 months.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except garnish.
Turn into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Garnish with tomato and parsley.

title: pico de gallo salsa
directions: Be sure all ingredients are finely chopped.
Combine ingredients and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 pieces of plastic wrap. Working out from center, pound with wooden meat mallet to form cutlets about 1/4-inch thick.
Peel off wrap and sprinkle each piece with salt.
Sprinkle scallions and parsley over cutlets. Place 1 stick of butter at the edge of each cutlet.
Roll meat around butter stick like for a jelly roll, tucking sides in as you go.
Press end to seal well.
Dust each roll in flour, dip in beaten eggs, then roll in fine dry bread crumbs.
Chill thoroughly, at least one hour.
Fry chicken rolls in deep, hot fat for about five minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with mushroom sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: wipes (baby, etc.)
directions: Cut roll of paper towels in half.
In sealed container, combine paper towels, water and baby wash or cleaning liquid.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the bouillon, wine, herbs, onion and green pepper.
Place rice, tomatoes and chicken in a large casserole; pour herb sauce over all.
Cover tightly and bake for 25 or 30 minutes.
Add seasoning. Turn off heat; allow to remain in the oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together in a large bowl flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cooking oil, eggs, shredded carrots, crushed pineapple with syrup and vanilla.
Mix together on medium speed until well blended.
Bake in greased and lightly floured pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add 2 1/2 cups boiling water to Jell-O.
Put in freezer for about 10 minutes or until Jell-O thickens a little.
Fold whipped cream and strawberries into Jell-O, alternating a little of each at a time until mixed well.
Tear cake into bite size pieces.
Put half of the angel food cake in bottom of an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of the mixture over the cake.
Layer the other half of the cake and pour remaining mixture over top.
Let set in refrigerator for about 2 hours before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: date bars
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and cream until light.
Add beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add dates and nuts; mix all together well.
Pour batter in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: frank's jambalaya
directions: Saute butter, celery, onion and peppers.
Add all other ingredients.
Place in covered dish.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
You can put pork chops, chicken or sausage in with rice to cook.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, margarine and sugar together well.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar well.
Spread over crust.
Slice bananas over cream cheese mixture.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over this.
Top with cherries and pecans.
Refrigerate for 8 hours.
(Drain pineapple before you start making cake.)

title: macedoine of fruit
directions: Combine and let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Strain and discard sugar residue.
Pour liquid over fresh prepared fruit, a mixture of 3 or more.

title: cole slaw
directions: Pour dressing over cabbage and/or optional vegetables and toss to cover.
Let cool to room temperature and refrigerate.
Stir to serve.
Keeps several days.
Great with cornbread and beans!

title: chess cake
directions: Combine cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg.
Mix thoroughly (will be very thick).
Press into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese, 3 eggs, sugar and vanilla. Beat with electric mixer until smooth and pour over crust in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely. Cut into squares.
Cake will fall as it cools, making thin, chewy squares.

title: tostada texas style
directions: Brown meat; drain. Stir in tomatoes, picante sauce, cumin and salt; simmer 5 to 10 minutes until most of liquid has evaporated. Cover bottom and sides of a 14-inch pizza pan with tortillas; spread with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with one cup of cheese; return to oven until cheese is melted. Arrange lettuce, remaining cheese, tomato and avocado over top. Cut in wedges and serve with additional picante sauce.

title: blackbeard's baked speckled trout(coastal carolina recipe)
directions: Cut fillets into serving sized portions.
Place in single layer in well-greased baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over fish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: melon delight
directions: Cut melons in half lengthwise and scrape out seeds, stringy pulp and some of the meat, leaving a shell about 1 1/2-inches wide.
Fill hollows with paper towels and invert on more paper towels to dry.

title: marinated tofu
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Add tofu. Marinate for 4 hours or longer.
Combine with mushrooms in skillet.
Simmer until done to taste.
May drain tofu and broil until golden brown or brown in hot oil in skillet, if preferred. Reserve marinade to re-use with tofu, meat or poultry.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: raisin spice cake
directions: First boil 3 cups raisins in 2 cups of water.
Drain juice off raisins and let juice cool.
(This is the liquid you use in the cake.)
Combine ingredients and pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes a large cake.

title: mid-eastern potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Toss all remaining ingredients with potatoes.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: jan's cream of tomato soup
directions: Saute oleo and tablespoon of onion.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, pepper and spices.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in 2 cups of tomato juice.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Stir in hot tomato mixture into 2 cups cold milk.
Heat almost to a boiling point and serve.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix together ingredients and put in airtight container and refrigerate.

title: chili (bowl of red)
directions: In Dutch oven, saute first 4 ingredients in hot oil until tender.
Add meat, 1 pound at a time, stirring until meat loses redness.
Drain.
Add water and remaining ingredients, stirring after each addition.

title: cornflake candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, pour Karo syrup.
Bring to a gentle boil. Add peanut butter.
Stir constantly until melted.
Remove from heat.
Spoon in cornflakes until too thick to stir.
Spoon mixture into a long pan that has been covered in Pam or butter.
Let cool and cut.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season chicken.
Dip chicken breasts in egg white and then roll in crushed corn flakes until coated well on both sides.
Place chicken on baking sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Large chicken breasts may take longer.
(A low-fat recipe.)

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Whip the oleo, sugar and eggs for about 10 minutes until fluffy. Add alternately the flour and milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a large tube pan for approximately 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and 1 cup pecans in large bowl. Mix well.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in the remaining pecans. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 of graham crackers. Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip together.
Pour over graham crackers.
Top with other 1/2 of graham crackers.
Spread chocolate icing over top.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: steamed brown bread
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over raisins; allow to cool.
Add salt, butter and sugar, then eggs.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Put all of this in large bowl.
Add flour gradually, mixing with hands.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Round up in greased bowl; turn to bring greased side up.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Punch down; let rise again until almost double.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Blanch broccoli and cauliflower in salted water and drain. Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs. Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with bread crumbs. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning package of Ragu and set aside.
Boil noodles until tender.
Drain.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In large soup pan, dissolve beef cubes into water.
Combine all other ingredients and simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar, oil and pumpkin, beating well after each.
Combine dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture, alternating with the water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer. Makes 2 large or 3 small loaves.

title: chip taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix taco seasoning and sour cream with beef.
Spread in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix together and spoon over 2 to 3 pounds of chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: grandma nulton's chocolate cookies
directions: Mix; beat and cook until it boils over low heat.
Add the vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Beat until thick and drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form 1 1/2-inch balls and lightly brown enough to seal all sides.
Remove from pan and set aside.
To the grease left in pan, add 3 bouillon cubes melted in 3 (beef) cups of water and 1 can chicken broth (small College Inn can).
Mix flour and water to make a paste and use this to make a gravy. After gravy thickens, add sliced mushrooms and 1 large container sour cream.
Stir well and add the meatballs.
Keep covered and use a low heat only to simmering and simmer for about 15 or 20 minutes. Serve over egg noodles or as is as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and marinate for 24 hours.

title: fresh coconut icing
directions: Mix egg whites and milk in pot.
Bring to a boil.
Take off stove and stir in salt, cream of tartar, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Put on cool cake and let sit in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Take out and top with coconut.
Put back in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: deer steak with mushroom gravy
directions: Place a sheet of aluminum foil in the bottom of a baking dish.
Allow enough to cover after putting steaks in. Rub seasoning into steaks.
Place steaks in dish and pour soup over them.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350 degrees for 30-45 minutes or until well done.

title: egg casserole
directions: Brown the sausage and drain.
Grease the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cube the decrusted bread and put on bottom of dish. Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over sausage and bread; sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover with foil, refrigerate overnight (must).

title: smothered steak with onions
directions: Put bacon in bottom of heavy frypan.
Place bottom of the round steak on top of bacon.
Put plenty of onions on top of meat.
Add water to cover.
Add salt and pepper and cook slowly for 3 hours. Add water later if it starts to lose water.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on for about 40 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool in cold water.
Peel carefully, removing skin only.
Add all ingredients, stirring carefully.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 8.

title: roasted pork tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Heat a large heavy skillet over medium heat, add butter. Add pork to skillet and sear on all sides. Place pork in a shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add jelly, apple juice and mustard to pan drippings. Cook over low heat, continually stirring until well blended, about 5 minutes. Spoon over pork. Roast pork for 50 minutes, basting every 10 minutes with pan juices. Cut into 1 1/2 inch slices, arrange on a serving dish. Keep warm. Blend cornstarch with cream. Place the baking pan on stove top over low heat, stir cornstarch mixture into pan juices. Cook, stirring until thickens, about 2 minutes. Serve over pork.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle onion on top of meat.
Pour soups over top.
Cover with the Tater Tots. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: white buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add a little buttermilk and beat until fluffy.
Sift all dry ingredients and add with the rest of the buttermilk and vanilla.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Pour into three 9-inch pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix together; salt and pepper to taste.

title: thanksgiving salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Cut orange and apples in very small pieces (I prefer to grind the apples).
Add sugar to fruit and let stand while Jell-O cools.
Just before it starts to set, mix in fruit and turn into mold or bowl.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Bisquick.
This must be added last.
Bake at 350° in a glass pie dish for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix together the soup mix, dressing and cranberry sauce.
Pour 2/3 of the mixture over the chicken breasts.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 hour.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken.
Bake 15 minutes or until done.
Serve with rice.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening (butter) and white sugar.
Add brown sugar and cream.
Mix in egg; make sure it is well mixed.
Then add baking soda and salt and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and mix.
Add flour and mix.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: apple-raisin salad
directions: Peel, core and quarter apples.
Chop into tiny cubes.
Add other ingredients and mix together.
Serve on a lettuce leaf.
Two apples serve 4.

title: fried lumpia(philippine egg roll)
directions: In 3 tablespoons hot oil, brown garlic, then add ground turkey or beef.
Cook until brown on high heat.
Reduce heat; season with salt and pepper.
Stir in green beans; cook for 1 minute, then add bean sprouts.
Stir and cook for 2 minutes.
Drain mixture and cool.
Wrap 1 tablespoon of mixture in each wrapper.
Deep fry in hot oil until brown.

title: jam cake
directions: Beat together.
Then add 1 tsp. cinnamon, 3 c. flour, 1 tsp. nutmeg, 1 tsp cloves.
Set aside.

title: chicken salad appetizer
directions: In small bowl combine chicken, chopped celery, almonds and onion.
Add mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice.
Mix well. Cover mixture with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1 hour or longer so that flavors blend and develop.
To serve, place 1 teaspoon of appetizer on "carrier" of choice.
Yield:
1 1/4 cups, enough for 36 servings on fruit, vegetables or crackers.

title: tricia's meat loaf
directions: Chop onions. Mix onions, Lipton soup mix, egg, ground beef and Tony's seasoning. Put 1 can of Hunt's Meat Loaf Fixings in the bottom of a loaf pan; put meat mixture in and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Pour other can of Meat Loaf Fixings on top and bake until hot.

title: apple pie
directions: Blend together sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt; toss lightly with apples.
Spoon into pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate.
Combine butter, brown sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over pie filling. Cover with lattice top.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: franke's salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and cool.
When mixture is partially set, add rest of ingredients.
Let set.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add vanilla, then remaining ingredients.
Roll dough into balls; place on a cookie sheet and flatten with a fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cake
directions: Roll pecans in 2 tablespoons of flour; mix all together.
Put in tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl until well mixed.
Place mixture into loaf pan or make several individual (small) loaves and place in covered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain excess grease from dish and pour as much catsup as desired on top of meat loaves and bake for 20 more minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: dressing meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into balls.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix 2 cans cream of mushroom soup and 2 cups of sour cream.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix flour, milk and egg to form a soft dough.
Knead about 20 times and roll out onto a well floured surface, adding flour to produce a manageable dough (1/4-inch thick).
Cut dough into 1/2-inch square.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten egg yolks, milk, margarine, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Deep dish is needed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: steamed salmon with parsley butter
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Top each steak with lemon or lime slices;
sprinkle
with
salt
and pepper.	Pour boiling water into
wok to reach 1/2-inch below steamer rack.
Place fish on rack.
Cover
wok and steam for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Remove to platter.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix melted butter and 1 tube Ritz crackers (crushed) and spread over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Start with frozen broccoli.
Follow directions on package. While broccoli is cooking, combine soup, mayonnaise and onion, then add broccoli, stuffing mix and packet inside.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no-cal spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
Use 1 teaspoon per cup water (5 calories).
Makes 50 servings.

title: strawberry balls
directions: Mix ingredients excluding one box of jello.
Then roll into balls.
Roll balls in other jello for color.

title: garden goodies
directions: Combine zucchini, carrots and flour; toss. Add mayonnaise, cheeses,

onions, basil and pepper; mix. Blend in beaten eggs. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool slightly; cut into squares. Serves for appetizer 4 dozen or can be used for side dish.

title: chicken livers marsala
directions: Dredge livers in flour.
Heat oil and butter in large frying pan.
Cook livers 4 minutes over high heat, stirring once.
Add onion and mushrooms; season and continue cooking 4 to 5 minutes over medium heat.
Pour in chicken stock; mix and cook 4 minutes over low heat.
Mix cornstarch with water; stir into sauce and bring to boil.
Simmer 2 minutes over low heat and serve with noodles.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Beat and pour into greased, large, low pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veal loaf
directions: Grind meat.
Blend all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, in 2 loaves.
Baste with hot water to which little butter has been added.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Or bake in 1 loaf about 2 hours, uncovered.
Before baking, brush top with slightly beaten egg whites.
Serve hot or cold.

title: caramels
directions: Cook until thick (in heavy pan) sugar and syrup.
Add oleo; let it melt.
Then add milk and cook at 245°.
Add vanilla.
Pour milk into syrup slowly, so boil doesn't stop--a must!

title: mrs. wintle's miniature tart shells
directions: Sift flour and salt; cut in shortening until the size of large peas.
Sprinkle water over mixture until smooth dough is formed. Roll on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch rounds to fit 1 3/4-inch muffin tins.
Prick!
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until a light, golden brown.

title: shake-a-snack cracker-snack
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a paper sack or a large plastic bag.
Pour 1/4 cup corn oil into bag and shake well. Store in closed plastic bag or a tightly covered container.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix
egg and milk together.
Dip chicken in mixture and roll in	crumbs.
Salt
and
pepper.
Melt
butter in dish and bake at 450° on each side.

title: grandma brown's impossible pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a blender, then add milk and Bisquick and blend on low speed 2 minutes.
Grease and flour deep pie pan; pour in mixture.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Drop shrimp into boiling water.
Boil 2 to 5 minutes.
Rinse, drain, peel and devein.
Saute onions, pepper and celery in oil; add flour and stir well.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and tomato juice.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add frozen peas and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: confetti salad
directions: Mix together; chill until soupy; then beat until fluffy.
Mix in:

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well.
Add flour (a little at a time) while beating.
Add vanilla.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Beat 3 minutes.
Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center is clean.

title: moist fudge cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
In saucepan, heat to boiling, butter, cocoa and water.
Add buttermilk, then add all ingredients in bowl.
Mix and pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Put icing on while hot right out of the oven.

title: fancy pork chops
directions: Brown chops in a little shortening; remove chops. Add onion and pepper (optional); saute carefully. Add your choice of soup with about 1/2 can milk; mix in skillet.
Place the chops in a shallow baking dish; pour soup mix evenly over chops. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes until chops are tender. May also be baked in a microwave.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and green pepper together.
Add remaining ingredients, except cornbread mix.
Simmer for 10 minutes on burner.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Prepare cornbread according to package; spread on top.
Bake at 350° until cornbread is done.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add mushrooms, pizza sauce, tomato sauce and oregano.
Mix altogether with cooked noodles in 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: dip for veggies or chips
directions: Mix all at once.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a boil for 1 minute sugar, cocoa and milk.
Take off heat and add butter, oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on a buttered pan.

title: quick and easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat chicken, soup, reserved broth and bouillon to boiling. Add cornstarch and drained vegetables; stir constantly until mixture thickens.
Add pimentos, salt and pepper.
If mixture is too thick, add additional broth; if too thin, add more cornstarch. Serve over hot biscuits.
Good with Jell-O salad and spiced peaches.

title: almost candy bars(easy 7 layer cookies)
directions: Cut margarine into the cake mix.
Sprinkle in a 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle both types of morsels, coconut and nuts on top of crust mix.
Pour entire can of milk over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until set.
Makes 48 bars.

title: dressing for hot potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat until warm in saucepan. Pour over hot, cooked potatoes.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Cook until it forms a hard ball when a small amount is dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Cool and drop on waxed paper.

title: maple baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight or for at least 8 to 10 hours.
Do not skip this step!
Beans may be purchased in Keene, NH.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mash bananas and beat in mixture.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into large greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
May be baked in 2 small loaf pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and take off bone.
Layer in pan.
Combine milk and chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Use chicken broth and mix with
Stove Top stuffing.
Spread stuffing over chicken that has been taken off bone and placed in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a one-quart microwave bowl, combine chips and milk.
Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Spread evenly into a wax paper-lined square pan.
Chill for 2 hours.
Turn fudge into cutting board, peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: ham and cabbage
directions: Wash
ham
and	put
in Dutch oven with approximately 2 quarts of water.	Cut the cabbage in 4 to 6 pieces, leaving a little of the hard center on each piece.
Wash cabbage and put on
top
of the ham.
Let cook in covered Dutch oven approximately 1 hour. Delicious and ready to eat.

title: pretzel bacon wraps
directions: Wrap one slice of bacon around each pretzel stick. Place on paper towels on paper plates, cover with paper towels.
Microwave on high for 2 minutes until bacon is crisp.
Arrange on tray and serve.

title: marinated cucumbers, onions and tomatoes
directions: Mix first seven ingredients in deep bowl.
Add sliced cucumbers, onion and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: sesame baked chicken
directions: Pour melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dip chicken in egg mixture.
Mix crackers and sesame seed.
Dip chicken then in the crackers.
Put in pan, coating them with the butter.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve with rice and Mushroom Sauce.

title: cold squash soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in squash and seeded lemon slice. Sprinkle with flour.
Cook 3 minutes over low heat, stirring, until all lumps are batter-floury.

title: kolaches
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; let the yeast dissolve in this mixture.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Let rise twice.
Use any filling you wish.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk together 1 minute.
Take off heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until peanut butter dissolves.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: baked beans
directions: I cook this in my slow cooker on low for 5 to 6 hours or bake in the oven for 2 hours at 325°.
This is a great recipe for large groups.

title: sausage potato casserole
directions: Fry sausage and drain well. In a bowl, combine soup, onions, peppers and milk. Layer sausage, potatoes and soup mixture. Keep layering until used up. Bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes. Last 5 minutes top with cheese and let melt.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs and blend well.
Stir flour and baking powder together.
Add to mixture.
Stir in flavorings.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Grease and line loaf pans with aluminum foil (3 small pans).
Place in cold oven and bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 250°.

title: griddle cakes(pancakes)
directions: Use
muffin
method
for
mixing.
Pour small amount of batter onto hot non-stick griddle or greased griddle. Brown on both sides to your liking. Top with butter and syrup.

title: spaghetti toss
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain; toss with sesame oil. Combine peanut butter, soy sauce and grated ginger root. Add to spaghetti and toss again. Voila! Good!

title: leek and potato soup
directions: In pan, melt 1/4 cup oleo; add 2 cups sliced fine leeks and the celery.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the water. Cover and cook about 10 minutes.
Add the potatoes and enough water to cover potatoes.
Cook about 15 minutes longer until potatoes are soft.
Add the milk and prepared kielbasa, cut in chunks.
Cook and season to taste.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In large salad bowl, combine cauliflower, olives, green pepper, pimento and onion.
In smaller bowl, whisk together lemon juice, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper.
While whisking constantly, slowly pour in oil.
Pour dressing over vegetable mixture and toss to combine.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Serves 8.

title: summer cheese cake
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in water.
To cream cheese, add sugar. Cream well and add juice of lemon.
Beat contents of Carnation milk until stiff.
(Have milk very cold.)
Add other ingredients and pour into cracker crust and chill overnight.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Heat the crushed pineapple and jello over low heat until jello melts.
Take off heat.
Add buttermilk, cottage cheese and cut up oranges.
Chill a little while, until mixture begins to thicken and cool.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into a bowl.
Save some of the oranges to put on top.
Makes a pretty dish.
You can decorate with leftover oranges, if you like.

title: angel cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Mix crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Press on bottom of spring-form pan.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Do not use mixer. Use large spoon.
Spoon into lightly greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add mashed bananas, salt and beaten eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder. Add to mixture.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: hot pepper mix
directions: In hot quart jars, pack with ingredients.
Boil vinegar; pour in jars and seal quickly with hot lids.
Ready to eat in 2 weeks. Really good aged for 9 to 12 months.

title: yummy yogurt cups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar until crumbly.
Sprinkle in water, one teaspoon at a time, stirring until dough forms.
Press about 3 tablespoons dough in bottom and up side of each of 4 ungreased 6 ounce custard cups to within 1/2-inch of top.
Bake until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Carefully remove from cups with small spatula. Let cool completely on wire rack.
Fill each cup with 1/3 cup yogurt.
Garnish with fresh fruit, if desired.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Mix all other ingredients in a large pot.
Stir in onion and beef.
Simmer on low flame for about 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.
I usually double the recipe to freeze some.
Serve on buns or over spaghetti.
I have used and given this recipe for over 40 years and all have enjoyed it.

title: corn-on-the-cob
directions: Put the ears of corn on individual sheets of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Brush with mixture of melted butter and salt and black pepper.
Wrap tightly.
Cook on the grill 20 minutes or so. Turn occasionally.

title: 3-cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Set aside aside.
Cook mushrooms until tender.
Cook stems until soft.
Dice stems and mix with cream cheese.
Add white American cheese and Mozzarella. Mix well.
Stuff mushrooms.
On top, add melted butter and toasted bits.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: coconut fingers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Using a teaspoon, shape finger-like, making them 1 1/2-inches long. Roll in remaining coconut. Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Put in layers as listed.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hershey bar fudge
directions: Boil sugar and cream for 4 minutes.
Put remaining ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour hot mixture over chocolate and Marshmallow Creme; beat until well mixed (use electric mixer). Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into buttered pan (large cake pan).

title: chess pie
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler. Add butter (use 1 cup milk).
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt. Add 1/2 cup cold milk, stirring until smooth.
Stir sugar mixture slowly into scalded milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thick. Beat eggs slightly.
Stir into hot mixture. Cook for 3 minutes longer. Stir constantly.
Cool slightly and add vanilla.
Pour filling into a 9-inch pie shell. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger, then add taco sauce and envelope of taco seasoning.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
While hamburger is cooking, combine cream cheese and onion dip together.
Spread this mixture in a pan.
After hamburger mixture is cooled, spread it over the cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until cool.
Just before serving, spread shredded lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and black olives over top of meat mixture.

title: oven-fried fish
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Rinse fish and pat dry with paper towels.
Measure thickness of fish.
Spray a shallow baking pan with nonstick spray coating; set aside.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine flour, egg, shortening, salt and water; mix well to form soft dough.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll out paper thin; let dough dry for 20 minutes.
Cut in small strips; drop in boiling broth.
Cook dumplings for 10 to 15 minutes, or until tender.
Add hard-cooked egg; stir lightly.

title: confetti pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, combine ReaLemon, oil, green onions and seasonings; mix well.
Add hot pasta; toss.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Garnish as desired.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces; pat dry.
Place in baking dish.
In bowl, mix other ingredients.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Mix baking powder and sugar together.
Gradually add sugar and baking powder to egg whites. Beat until stiff.
Fold in cracker crumbs and pecans.
Pour into buttered pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped cream.

title: squash au gratin
directions: Wash squash and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place in medium frypan with onion, water and salt; cover.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
In another pan, saute bread cubes in butter until toasty.
Spoon squash and onions into bowl. Sprinkle with grated cheese and toasted bread cubes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Place vegetables in greased casserole, adding salt and pepper to each layer.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Put beef on top of vegetables.
Make topping of soup, brown sugar and oregano.
Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: vicki's potato casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, onion, seasonings (may add some pepper, if desired) and 1 cup of the Cheddar cheese together in greased casserole with potatoes (which have been boiled to approximately half-done stage). Top with rest of cheese and crumbs and bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks thoroughly; add 1 cup powdered sugar and cream well.
Add flour, cocoa, salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a jelly roll pan lined with waxed paper.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven. Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes.
Turn out on paper covered with powdered sugar.
Whip cream sweetened with 3 tablespoons powdered sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread on cake and roll up like a jelly roll.

title: shrimp in garlic sauce
directions: Heat oil; saute garlic and shrimp over medium-high heat for 1 minute.
Add crushed red pepper, Tabasco sauce, paprika, sherry, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well until shrimp are pink and done.
Remove to a serving platter.
Sprinkle with parsley and garnish with lemon slices.
Serve with white rice.

title: faye's pound cake
directions: Cream softened butter and sugar with mixer.
Add eggs all at one time; beat until smooth and creamy.
Don't overbeat. Gradually add sifted flour and mace.
Blend until creamy.
Add vanilla and almond extracts.
Place in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
The flavor blends better if mixed and refrigerated for several hours or overnight.

title: old south cucumber lime pickles
directions: Soak clean cucumbers in water and lime mixture in crockery or enamelware for 12 hours or overnight.
Do not use aluminunware. Remove sliced cucumbers from lime water.
Discard lime water. Rinse 3 times in fresh cold water.
Soak 3 hours in fresh ice water.

title: camp suey
directions: Brown Hamburger with Onions and Flour in bacon fat.
Add the Celery, Kidney Beans with juice, and tomatoes.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on toast or cooked rice.
Brown rice is better. 8 Servings.

title: easy orange sherbet
directions: Put crushed pineapple through blender for a finer pulp.
Mix Eagle Brand condensed milk and pineapple in ice cream freezer and finish filling with orange soda. Freeze.

title: almond joy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In the microwave, in microwavable bowl combine condensed milk, chocolate and salt.
Cook on High for 5 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Stir after each minute.
Stir in vanilla and coconut.
Form cookies by dropping teaspoons of the mixture on a well-greased baking sheet, 1-inch apart.
Top each with a whole almond.
Bake on the middle shelf of the oven for 10 to 12 minutes, watching the cookies carefully after 8 to 9 minutes, as the bottoms can get too brown.
Immediately remove the cookies from the pan with a metal spatula and cool on wax paper-covered rack.
Freeze well.

title: quick chili con carne
directions: Cook beef, onion, garlic and seasonings in shortening until meat is lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover, cook over low heat 30 minutes; stir often.
Uncover; cook to desired consistency.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix together and bake in a muffin pan at 350° until brown.

title: martha white's basic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead just until smooth. Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with floured 2-inch cutter.
Place biscuits, lightly touching, on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes 12 to 14.

title: macaroni and stuff
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese.
Meanwhile, bring water, peas, hot dogs and margarine to a boil in large saucepan.
Stir in stuffing mix.
Cover, remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir stuffing mix into macaroni and cheese dinner.
Serve immediately.

title: quick banana bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine the oat bran or the pulverized rolled oats, flour, brown sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and nutmeg until smooth.
In another bowl, combine the buttermilk, oil, mashed banana and egg.
Stir the liquid ingredients into the dry ingredients all at once, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in the dates.
Grease 12 large muffin cups generously.
Spoon muffin batter into the cups.
Bake at 375° for about 18 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package and cool.
Melt oleo in skillet.
Add onions, celery and water chestnuts.
Saut 10 minutes (or until tender.)
Stir in rice, chicken, 1 1/2 cup cheese, and next 5 ingredients.
Spoon into greased dish, (13x9). Top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pastor's pancakes
directions: Pour pancake mix into mixing bowl.
Slice through mix with a knife, removing lumps.
Add eggs and 1 cup of milk.
Stir.
Mix should be thick or you may add remainder of milk for thinner mix. Add oil and stir again.

title: herb loaf italiano
directions: Thaw frozen dough for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at room temperature. Roll out to 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Combine butter, spaghetti sauce mix and parsley; spread on dough.
Roll up jelly roll fashion starting with long side; seal seam.
Place on greased baking sheet, seam side down.
Brush with water; sprinkle with a little salt. Cover and let rise until almost double, about 2 hours.
Make shallow slashes across top at 2-inch intervals.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate nut roll
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add syrup, milk, sugar, butter and salt.
Mix all ingredients together and boil slowly until forms a soft ball in water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and beat until thick. Pour on buttered dish.
Form into a roll on waxed paper.
Set in refrigerator and let cool and thinly slice in desired pieces.

title: 7-layer salad(use 9 x 13-inch pan)
directions: Combine these 4 ingredients and put on top of lettuce layers. Top with the remainder of the cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: gems
directions: Beat eggs slightly in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix at low speed until beaters gather dough together, about 2 minutes.
Form dough into balls with hands (teaspoon per ball).
Beat 4 egg whites with fork; dip balls and roll in finely chopped nuts.
This takes about 3 cups.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet and press thumb gently in center of each. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Fill center with icing.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft boil stage.
Stir in marshmallows until melted.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; beat 1 minute.
Pour into a buttered pan; cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Cook crust 5 minutes.
Then pour mix in crust and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 small pies.

title: peach crisp
directions: Arrange
peaches in greased 8-inch round
pan.	Combine oats, sugar, flour and butter.
Spread over peaches.
Bake
in moderate oven at 350° about 30 minutes.
Top
with
additional peach slices if desired.
Serve warm with whipped
topping
or ice cream.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in yogurt, marshmallows, grapes and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream. Turn into lightly oiled 9 x 15-inch loaf pan.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before cutting.
Slice and serve.
Return leftovers to freezer.

title: broccoli orange salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, raisins and pecans in bowl. Mix sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar; add oranges. Gently stir into broccoli mixture. Cover and refrigerate.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line a pan with tortillas, browned ground meat, onions, Ranch Style beans and cheese; then line with tortillas again. Pour cream
of
chicken	soup and tomatoes with chili peppers over
the tortillas.
Cover	with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
In another bowl beat eggs until foamy.
Add milk and vanilla gradually.
Stir until smooth. Add butter quickly.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Beat softened margarine until fluffy. Add sugar and continue beating. Add the melted unsweetened chocolate bar.
Add vanilla and keep beating.
Drop in the eggs, one at a time, beating for 3 minutes after each egg.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with the whipped cream and sprinkle nuts on top. Do not cook. Chill thoroughly and serve very cold.

title: double apple fantan muffins
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients; stir in 1/2 cup chopped apple.
Combine egg, salad oil and milk.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until brown.
Add beef and brown.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook 20 minutes covered. Add sour cream and garnish with parsley before serving. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: nutty apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a 9 x 5-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, mix peanut butter, margarine, egg and honey until smooth; set aside.
In medium bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and allspice.
Add oats and wheat germ; mix thoroughly.
Combine peanut butter mixture with flour mixture. Add yogurt, apples and walnuts; blend well.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 60 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Remove from pan; let cool.
Store in plastic wrap.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: frozen salad
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix according to directions on envelope.
Fold in sweetened condensed milk, then cherry pie filling and drained pineapple chunks.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan or dish; freeze until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Beat the sugar, shortening and egg, using high speed.
Blend in milk and sifted ingredients.
Gently fold in berries.
Spread batter in 8-inch square pan, lightly greased.
Sprinkle with Crumb Topping.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients together a little while.
In another pan, cook the carrots, salted and peppered to taste, until done (slice them however you like them).
When carrots are done, layer carrots, onion and pepper in a bowl.
Pour
hot sauce over all and cool in refrigerator.
Serve chilled.

title: pear chip preserves
directions: Boil 30 minutes kivered...now snatch the lid off 'n boil unkivered.

title: slimey limey punch
directions: Mix all
(except for the dry ice) - Dry Ice makes for a spectacular presentation.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and drop on an ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes about 12 dozen.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter, add eggs separately.
Add sugar (with mixer). Fold in flour, frosting and nuts by hand.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan (greased and floured).
Let cool completely before removing from pan.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Simmer until sugar dissolves.
Add 1 (6 ounce) can of pink lemonade.
Serve hot.

title: nettie's applesauce-pineapple salad
directions: Heat applesauce, add Jello, pineapple and juice.
Stir in nuts.
Chill until jellied.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream softened cream cheese.
Add onions and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Mix in 1/2 of chipped beef.
Shape into ball and roll in remainder of beef.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring the rice and water to a boil. Simmer, covered, until the rice is very tender and most of the water is absorbed, about 25 minutes.

title: stew made in oven
directions: Put all this in the roaster pan at the same time.
Cook for 5 hours at 225°.
Don't open oven until 5 hours are up.
If everything is not done, put it back in oven for 1 hour at 325° or at 350° until done.

title: pumpkin cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, softened with sugar, cinnamon, ginger, salt and nutmeg.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Stir in canned pumpkin, milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for about 45 to 50 minutes.
Chill. Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken breasts with marsala wine
directions: Remove skin from chicken breasts.
Ease flesh away from bones with a sharp knife.
Cut boned breasts in half.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper in a medium bowl.
Combine breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese in a small bowl.
Spread on aluminum foil.
Dip chicken breasts in beaten eggs, then coat with breadcrumb mixture. Let coated chicken stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt butter with oil in large skillet.
When butter foams, add chicken breasts.
Cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until chicken has a light golden crust.
Add Marsala or Port.
Cover skillet and reduce heat.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender. If sauce looks too dry, add a little more Marsala or Port.
Turn chicken several times during cooking.
Place chicken on a warm platter.
Taste and adjust sauce for seasoning, then spoon over chicken.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Make sauce with catsup, molasses, brown sugar and bacon drippings.
Add 2 tablespoons each onion, celery and green pepper. Mix well with beans.
Add Tabasco sauce and mustard.
Place beans in greased shallow Pyrex dish. Dice bacon slices and add to beans. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more. Serves 6.

title: buchanan family scottish shortbread
directions: Soften butter to room temperature.
Add sugar slowly until well blended.
Add flour gradually until all is used.
(May have to finish mixing by hand.)
Divide in half and place in 2 square (or round if necessary) 9-inch, ungreased pans.
Dough should be 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Prick with a fork all over and around the edge. Score with a knife the size you wish to cut when finished.
About 1-inch square works well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Let cool slightly before cutting with thin, sharp knife.
Should be stored in tin or Tupperware.

title: stove top stuffing
directions: Take 4 cups of broth made from the turkey neck, cook the night before and cool.
Use more, if needed.

title: german potato salad
directions: Put chopped onion in bacon grease.
Cook until it looks half done.
Add flour and cook until brown.
Then add sugar, vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil until thickens, then add potatoes and bacon. Stir, then remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix soups with 1 can cold water only.

title: radish and cream cheese spread
directions: Mix oleo, cheese, celery salt, paprika and Worcestershire sauce together until smooth.
Stir in radishes and onions.
Chill several hours to blend flavors.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: cordy cookies
directions: Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Set oven to 350°. Bake until done.

title: turkey-potato skillet dinner
directions: Trim fat from turkey and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Cook turkey, onion and mushrooms in vegetable oil until turkey is slightly brown and vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until vegetables are barely tender. Uncover and continue to simmer until most of liquid has evaporated.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 4 servings.
One-thousand calorie recipe.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix buttermilk with cake mix.
Add banana pulp and pecans. Mix and pour batter into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: halston torte
directions: Crush cookies.
Set 1/2 cup aside with remaining. Stir in melted butter.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Make up pudding with 4 cups of milk.
Mix both flavors together.
Pour over crust and chill.
